title: apple enchiladas
directions: Spoon fruit filling evenly down center of each tortilla. Sprinkle evenly with cinnamon; roll up and place seam side down in lightly greased 2-quart oblong baking dish. Bring butter and next 3 ingredients to a boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly for 1 minute. Pour over the enchiladas and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Add vinegar to milk to sour it.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to rhubarb. Set aside.

title: economy homemade ice cream
directions: Beat
egg
whites until stiff.	Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Use in an electric or hand-cranked freezer.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch or 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle Fritos on top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine all ingredients for meatballs.
Form into 1-inch balls. Place in a circular pattern on a round microwave-safe dish.
Cook at 100% for 1 1/2 minutes.
Rotate dish and turn meatballs over. Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Drain.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni by directions.
While that is cooking, dice the tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, cucumber up.
Can be mixed with salad dressing.
When macaroni is cooked, drain and run cold water over it.
Drain and mix.
Season to taste.

title: mounds
directions: Blend together.
Grease hands and roll mixture into small balls.
Chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip balls into mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: cantaloupe and raspberries with lime juice
directions: Peel cantaloupe, cut in half and remove seeds.
Cut melon into thin wedges and arrange on platter.
Juice the lime and drizzle over melon.
Toss raspberries with sugar in separate bowl.
Spoon evenly over melon.
Serve at room temperature.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chocolate cherry drop cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in cherries and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
If desired, garnish with cherries or walnut halves.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine brown sugar with margarine.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add milk. Let stand until lukewarm.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat until smooth.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend together and serve as a dip for your fruit salad.

title: lemon chicken with rice
directions: Saut onions in oil.
Add chicken and cook until tender and browned.
Add chicken broth; bring to boil.
Add carrots, broccoli and lemon juice.
Add rice; reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and cook until rice is fluffy and liquid is cooked away (not too dry).

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done, then chop or mash.
Add chopped pickles, chopped onions, chopped green pepper, chopped eggs, salt and pepper.
In skillet fry bacon until crisp, crumble and add to mixture.
Add mixture of vinegar, water and mustard. The more potatoes you use the more of all the other ingredients you will need.

title: cranberry puffs
directions: Will also need cupcake liners.

title: catalina chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in Catalina dressing overnight or several hours. Grill the chicken.
So simple, but delicious.

title: christmas wreath cake
directions: Bake desired cake in 12-cup ring mold.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on rack to cool. Cover with green frosting and then green coconut, sprinkled on frosting.
Add candied cherries in groups of 3 (for berries) to top cake.
Place large red bow on front center cake.

title: fish stacks
directions: Cut the fish into four 4 x 3-inch portions.
Place them in a shallow baking dish. Cook the onion, carrot and mushrooms in the margarine or butter, covered, about 5 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for 2 to 4 minutes or until excess liquid evaporates.
Remove from the heat. Stir in half of the cream cheese, dill weed and pepper. Spoon over each fish portion.
Separate crescent rolls into 2 rectangles and pinch perforations to seal. Cut each rectangle in half.
Place a rectangle atop each fish portion.
Brush the dough with milk.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: charlie's salsa
directions: Boil peppers until soft, then clip ends off.
Pull leaves from cilantro stems and wash.
Put all ingredients in a blender.
Run on chop until mixed thoroughly.
Salt to preference.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Spread mayonnaise over chicken.
Mix Parmesan and oregano well.
Roll chicken with mayonnaise in cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine coconut, crumbs, walnuts and butter.
Mix well.
Pat two-thirds of mixture into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon evenly over coconut mixture in pan.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut mixture. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool in pan, then chill.
Cut into bars.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Boil 2 quarts strawberries in 3 quarts of water.
Leave for 3 minutes and then drain off water.
Add 3 cups sugar to drained berries and boil for 10 minutes.
Add 3 cups sugar and boil another 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Place in clean, hot jars and lids.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together pineapple juice, almond extract and sugar.
Add ginger ale.
Three batches makes 2 gallons.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pie pan for 30 minutes at 350°, starting in cold oven.
There's no need for crust.
Delicious served with peppermint ice cream.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken on waxed paper and flatten to 1/4 inch.
Put a slice of ham and a slice of cheese on each flattened breast. Sprinkle with pepper, salt and parsley.
Roll lengthwise, start with the large end and use toothpicks to hold in place.
Dip in egg; roll in bread crumbs.
Melt butter in a skillet and brown on all sides.
Place in 12 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix the skillet drippings with the soups, wine and mushrooms and pour over chicken.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar and corn syrup; stir well.
Cook 4 minutes at High, uncovered.
Stir in peanuts and cook for 4 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla; cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda; mix well and spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Break into pieces when hard.

title: baked mayonnaise chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Combine mayonnaise, salt, pepper and garlic
salt.
Coat chicken; roll in crushed corn flakes. Bake
for 45 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350° and bake about 20 minutes more.

title: america samoa sweet bread(pao doce)
directions: Moisten yeast cake with 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar and stir until smooth paste is formed. Bring to a boil 1 cup of water, vanilla, lemon extract and milk until scalded.
Add butter and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and 1/2 cup of the lukewarm water.
Sift the flour; in a bowl, put 5 cups of flour.
Add liquid ingredients gradually, stirring and pressing out lumps with wooden spoon.
Beat dough vigorously and work it for 20 minutes.
Stir in 5 cups of flour and cover bowl. Place in warm place and allow dough to double.
Beat the eggs, taking out 2 tablespoons to brush tops of loaves with.
Add 2 3/8 cups of sugar to beaten eggs; stir them into dough.
Work in the bowl

with wooden spoon or hands for 15 minutes. Add 4 to 6 cups of flour and divide the dough into round loaves. Place each loaf in an oiled pan and allow it to double in bulk. Brush the surface of each loaf with the egg and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top
with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: lime gelatin-pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot pineapple juice.
When mixture thickens, add Cool Whip and rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook meat and set aside.
In butter, cook celery until it changes color; add onions and liquid to cover vegetables.
Bring to a boil.
Add meat, bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Serve with rice and noodles.
Serves approximately 4.

title: anna banana sipper
directions: Put water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Let cool.
In a blender, blend bananas and lemon juice (make into a puree).
In a large bowl, mix sugar water, bananas, pineapple juice and orange juice.
Stir well.
Put into freezer and let set. Thaw.
About 1 hour before serving, put into a punch bowl and break into chunks with fork.
Twenty minutes before serving, add 7-Up.
Makes 140 servings.

title: turkey dressing(low-fat)
directions: Crumble bread and mix with remaining ingredients.
Put in large baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: boiled custard (uncooked)
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on the box. Mix in Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 gallon milk. Refrigerate overnight.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins with enough water to barely cover until liquid is absorbed.

title: kielbasa and potato supreme
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into small cubes.
Place in large bowl and cover with water; set aside.
Slice sausage and cut slices in half or fourths.
Dice pepper and onion.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Drain water off potatoes and carefully place in skillet. Cover skillet and turn potatoes about every 7 to 10 minutes to avoid sticking, but not too often or they will be mushy.
When potatoes begin to brown, add remaining ingredients.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well.
Arrange in butter in shallow casserole dish.
Mix eggs, cottage cheese, onions, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, cheese and half the butter.
Pour over broccoli; mix remaining butter with crumbs and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine the cranberries and sugar.
Let set overnight.
Mix well the Jell-O and hot water.
Add and let set until congealed. Mix the nuts, marshmallows and pineapple.
Mix all together and chill overnight.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put zucchini, margarine and seasonings in a skillet.
Cover and cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 5 minutes, turning slices.
Sprinkle with cheese and toss.
Serves 4.

title: ranch style bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased loaf pan.

title: bananas 'n cream bundt cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add bananas and mix well.
Add flour to the cream mixture alternately with sour cream, stirring just until combined.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: bacon-stuffed potatoes
directions: Rub clean potatoes with oil and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until soft.
Allow potatoes to cool to touch.
Slice away skin from top of each potato.
Scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Saute shallots in butter until tender.
Add shallots and other ingredients to potato pulp and mix well.
Stuff shells with mixture.
Place potatoes in 9-inch square baking pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crunchy s'mores
directions: Spray a 15 by 9 inch pan. Mix chocolate chips, corn syrup, margarine and vanilla in a large bowl. Cover with wax paper and microwave on high 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until boiling; stir. Fold in cereal until completely coated with chocolate mixture. Fold in marshmallows.
Press mixture evenly into pan (slightly dampen fingers and press gently). Let stand about an hour.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together well.
Then mix other ingredients.
Put on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°.

title: gen's chicken soup
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Add flour.
Stir until blended.
Add milk and stir until milk begins to scald.
In soup pot, bring chicken stock to a boil.
Add milk mixture and chicken. Stir.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Carrots should be firm.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add mashed bananas and mix.
Add flour and soda.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour; grease and flour bread pan.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and fried bacon into pieces.
Mix with onions, raisins and walnuts.
Make dressing by mixing remaining ingredients.
Toss salad with dressing approximately 30 minutes prior to serving.
Chill until ready to eat.
Serves 8 generously.

title: wendy's sugar cookies
directions: Combine butter flavor Crisco (or like brand), sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Beat in egg.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Mix at low speed until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll out half of dough at a time, to about 1/8-inch thick on a floured surface.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Add colored sprinkles or leave plain.
Bake for 7 to 9 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and spoon off excess fat. Add next 7 ingredients to meat. Simmer, uncovered, until thick (30 minutes). Cook noodles as directed.
Combine cottage cheese with next 5 ingredients.
Place half the noodles in baking dish. Spread half the cottage cheese mixture over this. Add half the Mozzarella cheese, then half the meat mixture.
Repeat layers.
Place grated cheese on top. Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 375°.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: coconut date ball cookies
directions: Melt the butter, sugar and chopped dates in skillet.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Beat the egg, milk and vanilla; add to date mixture.
Cool 2 minutes more.
Pour over the Rice Krispies.
Add the nuts.
Let cool, form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: baked greek fish
directions: Have fish cleaned, scaled and skinned.
Wash thoroughly. Filet, if desired.
Rub fish with salt and pepper and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Saute onions in the olive oil till crystal clear.
Do not brown.
Add wine, tomatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Lay fish in a 9 X 13 X 2 stainless steel baking pan.
Add the tomato mixture over and around the fish.
Add about 1/2 cup more wine.
Add diced potatoes around the fish and sprinkle with the oregano, chopped parsley, sliced lemon, and sliced garlic.
Bake at 350° for about one hour or till the fish is flakey.
Never use aluminum pan because of the acid in the tomatoes and lemons.
"Bon Appetit"

title: cheese bread
directions: Make your favorite buttermilk biscuit dough up as if you were going to make biscuits.
Pinch off enough dough to roll out as if you were making pie crust, thin but not so thin as to tear.
Start at one side and put a line of butter and cover with sugar.
Roll up, repeating process until you have about 2 rows of butter and sugar.

title: army supper
directions: Fry ground meat until tender (an iron skillet is best).
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and salt and pepper.
When onion is transparent, add pork and beans.
Let simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Good served over bread.

title: hot cheesy beef dip
directions: Saute nuts in butter 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Chop dried beef finely and set aside.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Stir in beef, green pepper, onion, garlic and pepper and mix well.
Stir in sour cream. Spoon into 1 quart greased casserole.
Sprinkle nuts on top; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Yield: about 2 cups.

title: smooth potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on (easier to peel when boiled). Hard-boil eggs.
Chop and mix in large bowl.
Add chopped celery and chopped pickle.
Mix remaining ingredients in separate bowl until smooth; add to potatoes.
Top with paprika.
(I use dry onions, as onion taste doesn't get stronger the next day.)

title: streusel topped sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sweet potatoes, syrup and peel until well blended. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix flour, oats, sugar and cinnamon in a medium bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in pecans. Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes. Cooking time:
40 minutes.

title: corn beef hash
directions: Place potatoes in 10-inch skillet.
Cover potatoes with water. Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 6 minutes.
(Potatoes will be firm.)
Drain potatoes in colander; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wipe out skillet with paper towel. Add butter and onion; cook and stir over medium-high heat 5 minutes.
Stir in corned beef, horseradish and potatoes; mix well. Press down mixture with spatula to flatten into compact layer. Reduce heat to low.
Drizzle cream evenly over mixture.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn mixture with spatula; pat down and continue cooking 10 to 15 minutes or until bottom is well browned.
Top each serving with poached egg.
Serve immediately.
Garnish, if desired. Serves 4.

title: sylvia's chicken pie
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Place one can biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a large microwave safe bowl, melt chocolate at HIGH for one minute.
Stir and heat for an additional 30 seconds, or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter.
Gently "toss" crispex cereal into chocolate-peanut butter mixture until well coated.
Place confectioners sugar into a two gallon storage bag or grocery sack. Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag tightly.
Gently toss cereal mixture until well coated.
Eat and enjoy.
Store leftover in airtight container.

title: plain egg custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and salt.
Add milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake in a low oven (300°) for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover lightly and leave in cool, fairly dark place.
On second day stir with wooden spoon.
Fifth day, add 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1 cup milk.
Stir, cover and keep as directed.
Sixth day, stir.
Tenth day, add 1 cup each flour, milk and sugar.
Divide among 3 containers.
Give 1 cup to two friends.
Keep 1 cup.

title: banana-berry pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Mix in 1 cup of whipped topping.
Stir in 3/4 cup of sliced strawberries.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm, about 15 minutes.
Mix pudding with 3/4 cup of milk. Add 1/2 cup of whipped topping.
Chill 2 hours, then garnish with remainder of Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: frances' banana nut cake
directions: Note:
Use heavily greased Bundt cake pan.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Cook in preheated oven at 425° until lightly browned.
Cook about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: italian raisin cake
directions: Cook raisins in water 10 minutes.
Strain and reserve 1 cup liquid.

Add baking soda to reserved raisin liquid; set aside. Cream together butter, sugar, eggs, salt and spices until fluffy. Add flour and liquid alternately beating well after each addition. Stir in raisins and nuts; beat thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased 1-inch tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on rack before removing from pan.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: In large bowl, pour boiling water over oats; let stand 1/2 hour.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir salt, molasses or honey and butter into oats.
Stir in yeast. Gradually stir in 4 cups flour.
Knead in remaining 2 cups flour (dough still in bowl).
Shape dough in mound in center of bowl; cover with clean cloth.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, 2 to 3 hours.
Cut down with knife 6 or 7 times.
Divide dough in half; place each in well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan, pulling dough to cover bottom of pan.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when thumped.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: tortilla appetizer
directions: Mix first three ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over tortillas.
Roll and wrap tightly. Chill at least two hours.
Cut off rolled ends and cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: 7-layer southwestern dip
directions: Line a 12 inch platter with shredded lettuce. Stir together black beans, sweet pepper, and green onions. Spoon atop lettuce, leaving a lettuce boarder. Dollop sour cream atop bean mixture, gently spread in a smooth layer atop beans, leaving a boarder. Sprinkle jalapeno peppers and lime peel. Drain excess liquid from salsa. Stir in avocado, spoon atop sour cream layer, leaving a boarder. Sprinkle cheese on top. Top with a layer of chopped ripe olives and sprinkle with cilantro or parsley, if desired. Serve immediately or chill for up to 6 hours. Serve with Homemade Tortilla Chips or purchased chips.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together and put over pineapple.
Then put crushed crackers over the top.
Pour melted margarine or butter over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: burger bake
directions: Combine 1/4 cup soup with remaining ingredients except water. Mix. Shape into patties; place in shallow baking dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining soup with water and pour over meat.
Bake 10 minutes more.
Makes about 12 medium burgers.
Any leftover can be frozen for later.

title: diet dessert
directions: Dissolve jello and yogurt in boiling water.

title: skillet dinner(good and easy)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain grease.
Add gravy mix, water, garlic and uncooked rice and peas.
Cook until peas and rice are done, 15 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix and pour into prepared pie crust, graham cracker or regular.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, spread broccoli.
Dot with butter and place chicken in small pieces over this.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Grate cheese over this.
Bake at 350° until bubbles (about 20 minutes).

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions with nuts in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Combine condensed milk and cream of coconut.
When the cake is done, while it is till hot, punch holes in cake and pour the mixture of condensed milk and cream of coconut over the cake.
Pour as you punch holes.

title: cornell university chicken marinade
directions: Beat the egg, then add the oil and beat again.
Add seasoning while beating; add vinegar.
Pour over chicken and marinate for a day or two.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
On a large round platter, spread and layer ingredients in the order listed.
Chill well. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in one cup of boiling water.
Stir in cherry pie filling and let set until firm in 9 x 13-inch dish. Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water, set aside in bowl. Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Gradually add lemon jello mixture.
Stir in crushed pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Pour over cherry layer in dish.
Garnish with chopped nuts and refrigerate until set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Mix 1/2 stick oleo with cheese, stirring constantly.
Put broccoli in baking dish and cover with cheese mixture.
Crush crackers and mix in skillet with 1/2 stick melted oleo.
Brown and sprinkle on top of broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream and cheese. Spoon mixture into flour tortilla and roll up.
Place tortillas in greased baking dish. Chop onion and garlic.
Add to Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Pour tomato mixture over tortillas. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: almond roca
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 nuts in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Cover with 1/2 chocolate. Cook butter and sugar over medium heat for 15 minutes for hard candy, 11 minutes if prefer chewy.
Count time as soon as pan is put on stove.

title: summer bean salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in medium bowl, mix well. Combine rest of ingredients in small bowl and mix well. Pour dressing over bean mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Place broccoli in buttered casserole dish with rice, soup, Cheez Whiz and water chestnuts.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: golden glazed chicken
directions: In 13 x 9-inch baking pan arrange chicken skin side up and brush with butter.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes; baste with pan drippings.
Combine rest of the ingredients and spoon over the chicken.
Bake for 15 minutes or more until chicken is done.

title: aunties oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift flour with dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add oats and pecans.
Form into long rolls. Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 350° oven approximately 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool.
Put the Jell-O and the rest of the ingredients into a mixing bowl and mix with an electric mixer.
Pour batter into greased sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: warm coconut icing
directions: In a saucepan, heat sugar, liquid and butter until slightly thickened, 5 or 6 minutes after coming to a boil. Cool thoroughly in the pan. Add grated coconut.

title: lemon salad or dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, cool and chill until partly congealed.
Whip until foamy.
Add Cool Whip and lemonade.
Blend well.
Pour in mold sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate or freeze, garnish with fruit to serve.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Frost with cream cheese icing when cool.

title: party punch
directions: Put orange sherbet into punch bowl and stir in ginger ale. Add ice.

title: play dough for modeling
directions: Mix and knead all ingredients (except food coloring) until soft and not sticky.
Add more flour if it gets sticky.
Add food coloring to each part you want colored or leave white and paint with water-color or tempera.
Store in plastic bag or coffee can.

title: healthy pecan bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup of all-purpose flour.
In a large bowl, mix remaining 4 cups of all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, wheat germ, pecans, salt and yeast.
In a saucepan over low heat, heat water, yogurt, honey and margarine until very warm (125° to 130°); stir into dry mixture.
Mix in eggs and only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On lightly floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough in half; shape each half into smooth ball.
Place in 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Cover; let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled in size, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: orange-pineapple carrots
directions: In a small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, ginger and parsley flakes.
Add orange juice and pineapple.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Cook, stirring 1 to 2 minutes more. Stir in butter.
Pour sauce over hot carrots, stirring lightly to coat.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: vitner corn pops
directions: Boil butter, sugar and syrup for 5 minutes.
Add soda; mix well.
Put corn pops in a large pan (a roaster works well).
Pour syrup over corn pops and mix well.	Bake at 250° for 45 minutes. Every 15 minutes remove from oven and stir well.
Return to oven; repeat this 2 more times.
When done, spread out on wax paper or a brown paper bag.
Let cool.

title: texas pecan cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add well beaten egg yolks.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour, soda and lemon extract.
Beat well.
Add 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add 1/2 cup flour to candied fruit (I use red and green cherries) and pecans.
Coat well.
Mix into cake batter. Beat egg whites until they peak.
Fold into cake.
At this point it is better to use your hands.

title: microwave mashed potatoes
directions: Add cream cheese to mashed potatoes and mix well.
Stir in chip dip.
Add bacon and mix well.
Put in casserole; dot with butter and paprika.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.

title: marinated salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small flowerets.
Combine with sliced onion, mushrooms and celery.
Mix with other ingredients.
Let marinate overnight before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 weeks.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown meat; add pepper and onion.
Cook until soft.
Add mushrooms, tomato sauce, Prego and all the spices.
Cook spirals as directed.
Mix together with sauce.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat until well melted.

title: peanut butter cookie bars
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter.
Add brown sugar and mix well.
Add both eggs and mix until well blended.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended, then chips and nuts.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan and cut after cooled.
Makes 36 bars.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of mixer.
Add cream cheese, beating well until light and fluffy.
Alternately add flour and eggs, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crescent sausage 'n cheese bake(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Separate dough into 2 large rectangles.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2 up the sides of the pan.
Seal perforations.
Place sliced sausages over crust.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pollo relleno(stuffed mexican chicken)
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
Place each breast half between two pieces of plastic wrap.
Pound chicken to 1/8-inch thickness. Remove plastic; set aside.

title: may's date loaf candy
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to soft-ball stage. Add next 3 ingredients. While mixture is hot, sift powdered sugar into mixture until it makes soft roll. Wrap in buttered wax paper in form of log roll. Let cool overnight before slicing.

title: punch
directions: Add just before serving.
Add ice cubes or an ice ring.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla mix well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly and set aside.
Mix flour and sugar together and pour into medium saucepan, add milk and egg yolks.
Cook until mixture thickens, take off of heat and add butter and vanilla, mixing well.
Place 1/2 cup of peanut butter crumbles into bottom of baked pie crust. Pour half of pie mixture into crust.
Top with remaining peanut butter crumbles, reserving 2 tablespoons of crumbs for top of meringue.
Pur remaining pie mixture into crust onto crumbs.
Top with meringue.
Sprinkle remaining peanut butter crumbles onto meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until meringue browns.

title: dried fruit compote
directions: In large saucepan, combine fruits, sugar, clove and cinnamon with 6 cups water.
Bring to a simmer over medium heat, cover, lower heat and simmer until tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove lemons, cloves and cinnamon stick before serving, warm or chilled.

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup and water in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cook with microwave 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook 3 minutes longer. Beat in the evaporated milk and vanilla.
Recipe yields 3 cups.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder together; set aside.
Blend together butter, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Blend in flour mixture, then add other ingredients, vanilla and oats. Mix well.
Spread in greased sheet pan (with sides).
Add chocolate chips to top and mash into dough to make it level.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove; cool and cut into squares. Enjoy!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli with cold water; cut into small pieces, removing leaves and tough stems.
Blanch broccoli, cooking and boiling in water for 1 minute, then immediately drain and plunge into ice water to cool.
Cook bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Drain on paper towel.
Dice sharp cheese into small squares.
Peel and chop red onion.
Combine all ingredients, except bacon in mixing bowl.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and peanut butter; freeze.
Once frozen, roll into small balls and stick toothpicks into each ball.
Melt chips and wax.
Dip balls into hot chocolate mixture.
Let cool on wax paper.
Freeze until eat.

title: layered taco casserole
directions: With the exception of lettuce, this casserole has the texture and flavor of Mexican tacos.

title: gravy (microwave)
directions: Combine drippings and flour in 4-cup glass measure.
Add broth and beat with mixer until smooth.
Season to taste.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat well and continue cooking 1 1/2 to 3 minutes or until thickened.
Beat lightly and serve.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: company chicken divan
directions: Bone and shred chicken.
Cook broccoli using package directions.
Layer broccoli and chicken in greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder in bowl; mix well.
Spread evenly over chicken.
Combine bread crumbs and butter in bowl; mix well.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan, then pat in uncooked rice.
Add soup, rinsing cans with 1/2 can of water which is added to rice mix.
Add mushrooms, juice and almonds.
Salt and pepper chicken breasts; add melted margarine.
Cook at 250° for 3 hours.

title: quick cherry cheese ring
directions: Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and extract until smooth.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Separate rolls into 8 triangles. On large ungreased cookie sheet arrange triangles in circle. (Arrange in circle with pointed ends (tips), out and opposite ends (bottoms), overlapping slightly.)
Spoon cheese mixture onto bottom portion of each triangle.
Spoon cherry filling on top of cheese mixture.
Fold 1 triangle over so tip touches bottom corner. Gently press outside edge to seal seam.
Repeat.
Brush top of dough with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Purge crawfish, parboil and peel.
Set tails aside.
Mix vegetables and saute in margarine until transparent.
Add tomato sauce.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Add to vegetables; add crawfish and seasoning.
Bring to boil and boil 15 minutes.
This is now ready to serve over rice.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda; add shortening.
Crumble with your hand to make a good crust, then add enough ice water to make a ball of dough you can roll (just enough for a crust at a time). This is good for fruit pies.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: meal-in-a-skillet(weight watchers recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet.
Cook over low heat 20 minutes.
Each serving provides 3 P, 5 V and 1 B.

title: alpine chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish and mix carefully.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Dice carrot very small; slit onion and chop.
Soak mushrooms and chop.
Cut pork into small pieces.
Shell shrimp; devein and wash in salt water.
Chop into small pieces.
Boil rice until ready and let it cool.
Place 2 tablespoons oil into hot skillet. Stir-fry pork, mushrooms, carrots, pepper and shrimp (in the order indicated) with a few minutes pause between each of them.
Add soy sauce and remove from skillet.
Put 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Add rice; stir until coated evenly with oil.
Add salt; stir both mixtures and serve at once.

title: saucey steak skillet dinner
directions: *To shortening cooking time, use a more tender piece of meat. Coat beef with flour; pound into beef. Brown beef in oil. Push beef to side and stir in onion. Cook until tender and add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup. Mix liquid, catsup, sauce and spices. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and cook 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and green beans and bring to boil. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked stew
directions: Mix all together in baking dish.
Add raw meat, potatoes and carrots.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: melon cooler
directions: In a large pitcher, combine wine, or grape juice, melon juice and melon balls. Chill for at least 1 hour. Just before serving, add ice, stir, pour in club soda and stir lightly again.

title: deep dish onion potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and arrange in a deep dish casserole pan.
Melt margarine and stir in onion soup mix.
Drizzle this mixture evenly over potatoes and stir.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until soft.
Potatoes can also be microwaved.
Stir often and rotate dish until soft.

title: clam batter
directions: Roll clams in flour, dip in batter and fry in deep fryer.

title: pancakes (norwegian style)
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix thoroughly with a wire whip.
Pour small amount of batter into hot, lightly buttered 8-inch frypan, tilting frypan immediately to spread batter evenly.
Pancakes should be very thin.
Cook until light brown, turn and brown other side (adjusting heat as necessary).
Remove from pan and sprinkle with sugar.
Fold in half, then fold again. (Frypan can be lightly buttered as needed.)

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions.
Place in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cook in enough water to cover until tender; drain.
Crush crackers and mix crumbs with cheeses and margarine.
Put half of the crumb mixture in a casserole dish and put drained onions on top.
Pour evaporated milk over casserole in pan and top with the other half of the crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sassy cashews
directions: Lightly oil jelly roll pan. Toss nuts with egg white in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients; stir into nuts.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until caramelized. Spread in prepared pan.
Cool.

title: cornell barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, salt, poultry seasoning, white pepper and egg until all is well mixed. Place chicken in a large flat glass baking dish.
Pour marinade over.
Cover and let marinate overnight or at least 8 hours. Drain chicken on paper towels before barbecuing.
Place chicken on grill over burned down coals until chicken is browned and crisp.

title: persian rice
directions: Cook rice until tender.
Drain.
Mix butter, ginger and nuts; cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Mix with rice.
Place in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook, peel and cut potatoes crosswise into thick strips. Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add water to juice to equal 1 cup.
Heat juice to a boil. Add gelatin, brown sugar and salt. Stir until dissolved.
Add butter; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes and pineapple slices.
Simmer about 15 minutes; baste frequently until glazed and syrup thickens.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lime fruit salad(8 servings)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in medium bowl; stir in cold water.

Pour 1/2 cup gelatin mixture into bottom of 6 cup ring mold; refrigerate until set, but not firm, about 30 minutes. Arrange apple slices on gelatin; pour 1 cup gelatin over apples. Refrigerate until set, but not firm, about 45 minutes.
Refrigerate remaining gelatin until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites, about 45 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; spoon into mold. Refrigerate until firm, about 3 hours.
Loosen edge of mold with tip of knife; dip mold briefly in warm water.
Unmold on serving platter; refrigerate until serving time.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all well and bake at 325° until done.

title: ma waltz coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Carrots can be used instead of pepper, also 1/4 cup sugar and less salt.

title: carob chip cookies
directions: In blender, combine egg and butter.
Blend until smooth.
Add sweeteners and vanilla.
In a large bowl, mix together remaining ingredients.
Combine blender mixture with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in carob chips.
Drop on cookie sheet by teaspoon. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: hello dollies
directions: Layer these ingredients in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add last, stirring lightly.
Beat egg yolks well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes, or until lightly browned, then turn down to 350° and bake until set, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vienna tarts
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until blended and fluffy.
Add flour and knead to smooth dough.
Wrap in wax paper and chill for several hours.
Roll 1/8-inch thick into rectangle.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Place 1/4 teaspoon jelly in center of each; fold corner over and seal together tightly.
Brush with egg yolk, mixed with milk and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
You may use fruit or nut filling.

title: lo-fat brownies
directions: Stir everything together.
Pour and spread out into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: $100,000 starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Open one package solid chocolate mint candy wafers.
Enclose each wafer in about 1 Tbsp. of chilled dough.
Place on greased baking sheet about 2 inches apart.
Top each cookie with assorted sugar crystals, a walnut, or a pecan. Bake in moderate oven--375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: salmon quiche
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Pierce shell with fork on sides and bottom.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Melt butter; saute onion and mushrooms.
Add salt, lemon juice and dill.
Cook until heated.
Combine with cream, beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over salmon mixture in shell.
Sprinkle with cheese over the top.
Bake at 375° for 34 to 40 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine meats, crackers, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Shape meatballs by hand or use large ice cream dipper.
Place in baking dish.

title: quantity german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
When done, drain off water and set in refrigerator until cold.
Cook bacon and use 1/2 cup grease to saute onions until tender, but not brown.
Peel potatoes and put in large bowl.
Crumble bacon and put with potatoes, then add the hard-boiled eggs (chopped) to potatoes and bacon.
Stir or mix together.

title: julia beebe's pineapple pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar and the cornstarch into the crushed pineapple and its juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Spread cooled mixture into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Blend the cream cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add the eggs, one at a time; stir well.
Stir in the milk and vanilla.
Pour over the pineapple mixture; sprinkle with the chopped pecans.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then for 50 minutes at 325°.
Cool and hide from the family.

title: chip dip
directions: Chop up the dill pickles into small pieces (the amount of pickles depends on your taste; I find the dill chips work better than whole pickles).
Chop up onion into small pieces (this also depends on your taste).
Add the cream cheese and enough pickle juice to make creamy.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour pie filling into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the dry cake mix over the pie filling (store the rest).
Drizzle all of the melted butter over the top.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: baked carrots
directions: Drain carrots. Melt oleo in a pan with onion.
Let simmer. Stir in flour, salt, mustard, pepper, celery salt and cheese. Pour milk in gradually. Grease casserole.
Layer everything. Cover with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, cocoa and soda.
Mix vinegar and buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix food coloring with oil. Add to batter.
Bake in three 9-inch greased and floured cake pans at 325° to 375° for 25 minutes.

title: one pot chicken tetrazzini
directions: Blend margarine and onion powder in saucepan.
Stir in chicken and uncooked spaghetti.
Add mixture of broth, soup, lemon juice, nutmeg and pepper; mix well.
Sprinkle mushrooms on top; cover. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until spaghetti is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: pork chops gumbalaya
directions: Brown pork chops in oil.
Use the lid of your skillet to drain them in while you cook onion, bell pepper and soy sauce in skillet for 3 minutes.
Add water; bring to boil.
Add rice; lower heat and place pork chops in skillet.
Cover and cook on low about 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: date roll
directions: Bring sugar and milk to the soft ball stage (238°). When cool enough to handle, form these ingredients into a roll with buttered hands. Wrap the roll in a damp cloth or in waxed paper. Chill and slice.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Tear cake into chunks and place into a large glass bowl. Combine dry gelatin with strawberries and mix well. Pour over cake. Pour prepared pudding on top of strawberry mixture. Add sliced bananas, then whipped topping on top. Garnish with fresh sliced strawberries in the spring and summer. Sliced maraschino cherries can be used in the fall and winter.

title: pudding finger paint
directions: Rubber band several crayons together, with coloring tips even. Use to color rainbow stripes or any variety of multi-colored creations.

title: jalapeno eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cook eggplant in small amount of water until tender. Mash with slotted spoon.
Saute onions in bacon drippings or vegetable oil until tender.
Add mashed eggplant, seasoning and remaining ingredients.
Pour in greased casserole and top with bread or cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa; add milk and egg yolks.
Cook over low heat.
When started to boil, add butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
Add 8 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Put on pie.
Brown the meringue about 10 minutes at 325°.

title: roast beef mac and cheese
directions: Put roast in a large and deep baking dish.
Chop onion and put it on top of roast; cube cheese and put on top of that. Then pour tomato juice over all and put in a preheated 350° oven. Make sure to cover with lid or foil.
Cook until done or until tender, around 4 hours.
Take out of oven and put macaroni in and stir until all macaroni is covered.
Return to oven and cook until macaroni is tender.
Let stand a few minutes and enjoy.

title: squash dressing
directions: Melt oleo, add chicken soup, celery, sage, and (cut up pieces of chicken, if desired).
Bake at 400 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: yummy mint brownies
directions: Bake brownies according to package directions, but remove a few minutes before finished.
Sprinkle broken mint bits on top, spacing evenly.
Return to oven for remainder of baking time, to allow mints to soften.
Remove from oven and immediately spread melted mints with a table knife.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: seven-up pancakes
directions: Mix oil, egg and 3 ounces 7-Up with electric mixer.
Then add Bisquick and 2 ounces 7-Up.
Mix well.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Lay coconut out to thaw when you start baking the cake.
Bake in two 9-inch pans.
When cake is cool, remove from pans and slice each layer in half, making 4 layers.
Then beat the whipping cream until stiff.
Add 1 cup sugar and beat until sugar is dissolved. Add 2 packages coconut and mix well.
Divide this filling into 3 parts and stack layers, putting this filling between each layer. Beat the frosting mix until stiff.
Don't underbeat.
Spread over entire cake, then add the other 2 packages coconut.
Sprinkle over all the cake.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Heat rice and water to boiling, stirring once or twice; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 14 minutes.
(Do not lift cover or stir.) All water should be absorbed.
Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir in sugar, raisins, milk, vanilla, salt and hot rice; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill well and serve.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add seasoning, water and olives and simmer 5 minutes. Add sour cream. Press unrolled crescent roll dough into 10-inch pie plate. Pat 1 cup crushed Fritos in bottom of crust. Pour meat mixture on chips and sprinkle cheese on top. Sprinkle remaining chips on top. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt butter in pan and cook chicken.
Add garlic and lemon. Drain grease.
While chicken is cooking, cook noodles and drain. Combine chicken and noodles and add cream, cheese and wine.
Mix well.

title: chicken delight
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top chicken breasts with cheese. Top with soup, mixed with water, then broccoli.
Melt butter; mix with water into stuffing and sprinkle.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Combine milk, 1 c. sugar, margarine, flour, baking powder. Add berries. Add juice or water. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Sprinkle 1 c. sugar over top. Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes.

title: hamburger noodles stroganoff
directions: Melt butter.
Add beef, onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until meat loses its red color, stirring with fork to break up meat.
Add wine, lemon juice, bouillon cubes and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add noodles, cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until noodles are tender, adding more water if necessary.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and heat gently.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; drain and put in casserole.
Add thawed and drained broccoli.
Saute onions and celery in the butter.
Put into casserole.
Combine soup and cheese.
Pour into casserole and mix all ingredients until well blended.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken yucatan*
directions: Season
chicken
breasts
with spices.
Line a flat pan with aluminum
foil.
Place chicken in pan, distribute onion, celery, tomatoes
and
pepper
over
chicken.
Pour in orange juice and marinate several hours.
It's convenient to do this in
the morning
and
forget until mid-afternoon.
Cover with foil and bake
at 300° for 4 hours.
Serve over saffron rice. Slow, long cooking very important.
Serves 8.

title: walnut bourbon candy
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix vanilla wafers, confectioners sugar, walnuts and cocoa.
Mix in bourbon and corn syrup.
Mix well, adding a little more bourbon, if too dry.
With hands, roll mixture into 1-inch balls, then roll each
into granulated sugar. Store tightly covered.
Makes about 36 candies.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Cook 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and let set until cool.

title: copper penny(marinated carrots)
directions: Cook sliced carrots; don't overcook.
Drain and cool.
Mix remaining ingredients together, folding over cooled carrots. Cover, let stand for at least 12 hours.
It will keep in refrigerator for weeks.
Serve cold or at room temperature.

title: baked noodles
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter in double boiler and add flour and milk to make a cream sauce.
Add cheese spread until melted.
Set aside.
Melt 1 stick butter in pan with bread crumbs.
Spread drained asparagus on bottom of baking dish and add drained peas.
Spread 1/2 of bread crumbs over peas.
Add drained mushrooms.
Pour cheese sauce over mixture and sprinkle remainder of bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in water.
Fold in other ingredients after jello is tacky on top.
Use a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in the fridge.

title: chicken and ham lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, saute the mushrooms, onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in flour until blended. Gradually add milk and broth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in broccoli, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Spread 2 cups broccoli mixture in a greased 13 x 9 baking dish.

Top with 4 noodles, overlapping if needed. Layer with 2 more cups broccoli mixture, 1 1/2 cups of ham, 2/3 cup Swiss cheese, 4 noodles, 2 cups broccoli mixture, chicken, 2/3 cup Swiss cheese, 4 noodles and remaining broccoli mixture, Swiss cheese and ham. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until heated through. Let stand 15 minutes before cutting. Yields 12 servings.

title: surprise stuffing
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add to finely crushed soda crackers. Add beaten egg, seasonings.
If mixture is too dry, add boiling water a little at a time.
This mixture will be sufficient to stuff a 10 lb. turkey.
Delicious and moist!

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium sized bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in bowl.
To assemble, spread bean dip on large shallow serving platter; top with seasoned avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream-taco mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes and olives; cover with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: corn biscuits
directions: Melt margarine	in
baking
pan.
Mix Bisquick and corn together.
Mix well.
Knead until can handle easily.
Roll out and cut into strips.
Put in margarine and turn over to butter both sides.
Bake
as you do biscuits at 450° until browned as desired.

title: barbecued kolbassi
directions: Cut kolbassi into slices.
Cook in water until water boils, then let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients with mixer.
Pour into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
After removed from pan sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken and let cool.
Take off all fat and bone.
Season with garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Add half can of the enchilada sauce, half of the cheese, half can of black olives and half of the diced onion.
Fry up tacos, just so they are soft.
Drain. Arrange in casserole dish, fill with mixture and then top remaining ingredients over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with lettuce and tomato on side.

title: delicious rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add brown sugar, salt and 1/2 cup white flour.
Mix and let stand for 20 minutes.
Into a large bowl put the liquid mixture of milk and malt.
The chocolate malt gives rye bread a nice color.
Mix together with this:
molasses, oil, salt, caraway seed, orange rind and rye flour.
Add the first sponge mixture and stir well.
Add enough of the white flour to make a dough stiff enough to knead and not be sticky (about 2 cups).
Knead well.
Grease bowl well and put in dough.
Let rise about 2 hours and punch down once.
Mold into 3 loaves.
Let rise again.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rosy glow cranberry punch
directions: In large saucepan combine all ingredients; mix well.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot in mugs with orange slices floating on top or with cinnamon sticks as stirrers.
Makes 14 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: cubed steak
directions: Mix flour and water thoroughly for thickening.
Brown steaks on both sides, then dip in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook celery ahead of time, then add to broth and add both to steaks.
(You need a large turkey roaster or an electric roaster for this amount.) Chopped onion is available, but not too much.
Bake until very tender (2 or 3 hours).
After cooking about an hour, add some thickening.
Don't use too much, just to slightly thicken juice. When serving, add thickened juice to each serving.
Servings should all be the same size, one per person.

title: parmesan potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Cook potatoes in water, covered, 15 to 20 minutes until tender.
Drain well and return to pot.
Add butter to potatoes and mash until butter melts.
Add milk, eggs, cheese, parsley, salt and pepper and mash until smooth (some small lumps may remain). Spoon into prepared dish.
May be made ahead to this point and refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature before baking.
Bake covered 45 to 50 minutes until puffed and golden.
Makes 12 servings.
Very easy and delicious!

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan; add honey, lemon juice and peel. Coat both sides of chicken pieces with mixture and bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour on each side.
Baste occasionally.
Bake until tender in moderate oven at 350°.

title: mashed sweet potato bake
directions: Cook peeled sweet potatoes in boiling water until done.
Drain and cut up; mash with electric mixer.
Add orange peel, orange juice, brown sugar, butter, salt and cinnamon.
Add egg and milk; beat until fluffy.
Bake at 350° in a greased 1-quart casserole covered for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix in taco seasoning and water. Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer in casserole with taco chips and cheese. Repeat until casserole dish is full.
Top with enchilada sauce. Heat in 350° oven until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.

title: cheesy squash souffle
directions: Cook sliced squash in a small amount of water until tender. Drain and set aside.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet; saute onion until tender.
Remove from heat; add squash and next 3 items, mixing well.
Spoon into lightly greased 2 quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden.
Yields 6 servings.

title: walton's homemade candy
directions: Combine all ingredients; knead until smooth.
Roll into small balls; dip in chocolate, if desired.
Yield:
50 balls.

title: piquant ham loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine meats with remaining loaf ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack into 8 1/2 x 4 1/4-inch loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes.

title: gob cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Divide cake into two 9 x 13-inch pans, greased or put wax paper on them.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Put Gob Icing between the 2 cakes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift all dry ingredients together and stir into egg mixture until well blended.
Add raisins and nuts, after rolling them in flour to make sure they mix well.
Pour batter into 2 (8 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until done.
When done, remove from oven and allow to cool 10 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt; set aside. Combine sugars and shortening; cream until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Beat for 5 minutes and pour in buttered pan (9 x 13-inch). Put in refrigerator until cold and cut into squares.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix eggs, milk, whiskey and butter. Pour in cake mix and pudding. Beat all ingredients. Add 1/2 the chocolate chips and pecans. Pour batter into a 13x9 inch pan; sprinkle remaining chips and pecans over the batter. Bake at 350° for about 1 hr.

title: pulled taffy
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients together until mixture turns brittle when dropped in cold water.
Add vanilla and soda.
Pour into buttered platter.
Turn in edges and when cool, pull until white and brittle.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat water, sugar, spices and margarine in pan until sugar dissolves and margarine melts.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Cut dough into 12 equal pieces.
Roll out dough for 12 dumplings.
Place in small aluminum pie tin.
Fill with apples that are peeled and cut into small chunks.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and dot with butter.
Pinch top together and pour syrup over dumplings.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: rhubarb surprise
directions: Bring to a boil the rhubarb, water and sugar.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows.
Add jello to rhubarb.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cover chicken with water; add all other ingredients, except for dumplings, and cook until chicken is tender.
Strain stock and discard vegetables.
Remove chicken from bones and add back to stock.
Make dumplings by mixing flour, butter and milk.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling chicken stock.
Cook until dumplings are done.
Adjust taste with salt and pepper.
Thicken with flour and milk.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice mix according to package directions; set aside. Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add onions, celery, and water chestnuts.
Saute 10 minutes or until tender. Stir in rice, chicken, 3 cups cheese, soup, and next 4 ingredients. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 15-inch by 10-inch baking dish or a 4-quart casserole.
Top casserole evenly with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; sprinkle with remaining 1 cup cheese; bake 5 more minutes.

title: sardine spread
directions: Drain sardines and mash.
Season with other ingredients. Serve on bread rounds, toast or crackers.

title: fish granada with bananas
directions: Place fish in large skillet.
Add wine, salt and pepper, lemon juice.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 5 minutes or until just done.
Spoon liquid over fish frequently. Lift fish from skillet gently.
Place on oven proof platter. Cover and keep warm.
Reserve 1 c. liquid from cooking fish.
In top of double boiler, beat eggs until slightly thickened.
Place over simmering water.
Add butter; cook stirring constantly 2 to 3 minutes.
Slowly add reserved liquid.
Peel and slice bananas, arrange over each fish.
Cover with sauce and broil until golden (about 2 minutes).

title: german meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, mixing well.
Add ground beef and mix thoroughly.
Shape into a 9-inch loaf pan; place on a lightly greased rack of a broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Put into saucepan the carrots, sugar, water, raisins, margarine, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir until blended.
Pour into 9-inch mold.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: brunch treat
directions: Place bread, sausage and Cheddar cheese in 9 x 13-inch casserole in layers.
Mix together eggs and 1 cup milk and pour over layers.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: lazy day duff
directions: Melt butter in 8-inch baking dish.
Sift together sugar, salt, baking powder and flour.
Add milk and stir.
Pour batter over butter.
Do not stir.
Pour fruit over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.

title: mexican corn soup
directions: Combine the corn and 1 cup chicken stock in blender.

Melt the margarine in pan. Add corn mixture and cook slowly for 5 minutes. Add the 2 cups chicken broth, minced garlic, salt, pepper, oregano and chopped chilies. Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
May be frozen at this point.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Heat and serve.

title: old-time buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda into bowl.
Add shortening and cut in with pastry blender or two knives until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk all at once; stir until dough follows fork around bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured surface; knead 1/2 minute.
Roll 3/8-inch thick; brush with melted fat.
Fold over and cut double biscuits.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven (450°) 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 to 16 biscuits.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Then drain grease.
Mix all ingredients in pan with hamburger.
Cook on medium for about 1/2 hour.

title: green rice
directions: Boil broccoli as directed.
Heat Cheez Whiz in microwave.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° until hot.
May be topped with bread crumbs before baking.

title: party crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook and drain grease from hamburger meat. Stir in soup mix and cheese mix well. Separate rolls place a tablespoon of meat mixture in center triangle, fold over and seal edges. Place on a baking sheet bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: You will need a glass measuring cup and 9-inch glass pie plate.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans on platter.
Spread avocados over bean layer.
Mix sour cream and taco mix together.
Spread over beans and avocados, covering completely.
Sprinkle grated cheese, onions and olives over top.
Chill at least one hour.
Serve with taco chips.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg and bananas together.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Roll in chopped parsley, dried beef or salted nuts.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cut up and dissolve Circus peanuts in jello.
Drain pineapple.
Use juice to make 2 cups of cold water (if not enough juice, add water for 2 cups).
Add to jello.
Refrigerate until partially set, then add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Place in decorative bowl or mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes. Pierce skin with large fork 3 to 4 times.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
Slice potatoes in half lengthwise. Scoop out meat of potatoes with metal spoon, being careful not to tear the skin.
Place meat of potatoes in small-medium bowl.
Place potato skins on baking sheet.
Mash potatoes with potato masher. Add milk and margarine
and whip using portable electric mixer.
Add additional milk as needed to reach whipped consistency.
Just before quitting, season with salt and pepper.
Using metal spoons, scoop mashed potato mixture back into potato skins.
Use all of the mashed potato and all of the skins.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Put under broiler for about 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Watch carefully!
Garnish with paprika.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Peel cucumbers and slice thin. Combine remaining ingredients and mix.
Cover and chill.

title: santa's whiskers
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla. Stir in flour, cherries and nuts.
Form into 2 rolls, each 2-inches in diameter and 8-inches long.
Roll in coconut.
Wrap and chill several hours or overnight.
Slice 1 1/4-inches thick. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown.
Yield: About 5 dozen.

title: richard sterben's shrimp marinara
directions: Cook pasta with 1 tablespoon oil.
Set aside.
Saute garlic, basil, oregano, onion and pepper in olive oil for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and simmer 20 minutes. Salt to taste.
Serve over pasta.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Cream together butter and all above ingredients.
Mix well; will be a little difficult.
Chill in fridge 2 hours.
Drop by tablespoons on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.
Makes about 180 cookies.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove pulp, reserving skins.
Place pulp in mixing bowl.
Add onion, salt, pepper, margarine and egg.
Beat well, until fluffy.
Refill potato skins and arrange in a shallow baking dish with cut sides up.
Spoon sour cream over each half. Bake 10 minutes, until tops are lightly browned.

title: merry cherry bars
directions: One 16 ounce package of M&M's yields about 1/2 cup green candies.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese, green onions, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on round flat dish.
Spread chili sauce over cheese mixture and top with shrimp.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: butter cups
directions: Cream butter until soft.
Add sugar and beaten eggs; mix thoroughly.
Mix and sift dry ingredients. Add to creamed butter and sugar.
Add flavoring; mix well.
Put into pastry bag; squeeze onto greased cookie sheet.
May be dropped by teaspoonful.
Bake in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crumpets
directions: Mix yeast with the sugar.
Add water and let stand for 5 minutes until foamy.
Stir in the milk, egg and 1 tablespoon of the butter.
Add flour and salt.
Mix until well blended, cover with damp towel and let stand in warm place until doubled (about 45 minutes).
Brush the insides of 4 three-inch flan rings (or tuna fish cans with both ends removed) and the bottom of a heavy frying pan with melted butter.
Over low heat, heat the rings in the pan and then place about 2 tablespoons of batter into each.
Cook for 7 minutes, or until holes appear and the tops are dry.
Then remove the rings and turn the crumpets to brown them lightly on the other side (about 2 minutes).
Repeat the process with the remaining batter.
Crumpets are best served warm, but can be cooled on a wire rack and toasted just before serving.
Yield 6 crumpets.

title: easy berry cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour half of the flour mixture in dish. Add berries, then remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut crinkles
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening until soft.
Add sugars gradually, continuing to cream until light and fluffy.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Add 1/3 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Chill dough 10 minutes.
Pack dough into cookie gun; make in various shapes on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in hot oven at 400°.

title: party mix
directions: Combine Rice Chex, raisins and mixed nuts.
Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour over dry mix.
Pour powdered sugar over and mix well.

title: oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine potato strips, vegetable oil, and salt in a large bowl, and toss well. Arrange the potato strips in a single layer on a baking sheet. Bake at 450 degrees for 35 minutes or until fries are golden. Yield: 4 servings, 3.6 points.

title: butter almond-chocolate cake
directions: Saute nuts in butter in saucepan until golden; reserve 1/4 cup for garnish.
Add sugar, milk, yolks and salt to remaining nuts in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat to boiling; simmer 1 minute, or until lightly thickened.
Add vanilla; chill.
Beat whites until stiff; fold in chilled mixture, then whipped topping.
Freeze until firm in 8 or 9-inch layer pan (depends on size of cake layer), lined on bottom and sides with waxed paper at least 4 hours.
Split cake layer, making 2 thin layers; place one on serving plate.
Unmold frozen mixture onto layer; top with second layer.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and reserved nuts. Store cake in freezer; let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels and Pet milk in double boiler.
Add pecans. Place on buttered cookie sheet in refrigerator for one hour.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
If too thick, add more paraffin. Dip caramels into this.

title: onion fried chicken
directions: Place the chicken in a shallow baking dish and sprinkle with thyme and soup mix.
Pour the French dressing over chicken to coat and cover with foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for one hour.
Uncover and bake for 30 minutes longer or until brown.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine chocolate bits, evaporated milk and butter in a small saucepan.
Cook over low heat until mixture is creamy and smooth. Combine remaining ingredients and gradually stir in the chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in oven at 275° for 40 minutes or until firm.
Cool pie completely before covering with plastic wrap.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Bring to a rolling boil the sugar and syrup.
Add peanut butter.
Pour in cereal.
Mix well.
Pack into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt slowly the butterscotch and chocolate together.
Spread over mixture. Let set.
Do not refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: clam and meat loaf
directions: A little more of the cracker meal may be used depending on the amount of liquid with the clams.
Mix all ingredients together very well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mother's cheese cake
directions: Add cream cheese mixture to hot Jello. When cool, add to whipped Milnot. For bottom/topping, mix graham cracker crumbs, margarine, and powdered sugar. Reserve 1/2 cup. Place rest of crust mix in a large pan. Add Jello mixture. Sprinkle top with reserved crumb mixture. Refrigerate for several hours before serving. May be served with fruit.

title: grape drink(to can)
directions: A delicious bright red grape drink can be canned when the Concord grapes are ripe.

title: italian cheese-it casserole
directions: Cook meat and seasonings in skillet until pink color disappears.
Drain well.
Spoon into a 2-quart baking dish.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Cook chicken, cut into chunks and put into a 12 x 9 inch baking dish.
Add onion flakes.
Combine milk and soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bake tater tots according to directions on package.
When done, top hot dish with tater tots and cheese.
Bake until hot.

title: texas caviar #2
directions: Drain black-eyed peas and put in bowl and add all vegetables. Mix in Italian dressing, wine vinegar and spices to taste.
Make this recipe several days in advance of serving.
It is like us old folks; it gets better and better with age.
Feel free to add or delete ingredients to your liking.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, put flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt and mix together.
Make 3 holes in the mixture.
Into the first hole, pour the Crisco oil.
Into the second hole, pour the vinegar.
Into the third hole, pour the vanilla.
Then pour the water over the whole mixture.
Beat in the pan until nearly smooth and you can't see the flour.

title: oven baked corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour in well-oiled pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Chop pepper, onion and celery.
Combine the remainder of ingredients and cook for 30 minutes.
If mixture is thin, add about 2 tablespoons flour and cook another 30 minutes.

title: never fail rolls
directions: In large mixer bowl, add and mix ingredients in the order given, beating slightly after each addition.
Add flour gradually, not all at once.
When dough becomes thick, remove beaters and use a spoon to stir in last of flour.
When dough is soft, but not too firm, transfer to a large oiled bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
About 2 hours before cooking, put dough on a floured surface adding enough flour to handle and knead slightly.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with small floured cutter and place on a greased baking pan.
Brush melted margarine on top. Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° 8 to 10 minutes.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Take out 1/2 cup crumbs and set aside.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Blend all of the ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrots and ranch dressing
directions: Take a clean scrubber pad and scrub carrots clean. Chop off the ends. Ready to eat. Dip in Ranch dressing.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Stir rest of ingredients into macaroni.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pay day cake
directions: Mix oleo, egg and cake mix and bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.
While hot, put 3 cups miniature marshmallows on top.
In saucepan, combine corn syrup, oleo, peanut butter chips and vanilla.
Cook on low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Then add 2 cups Rice Krispies and peanuts. Spread on cake.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Tang and sweetened condensed milk; stir in sour cream. Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Pour into pie crusts. Refrigerate at least 8 hours.
You can cover pies with extra Cool Whip and decorate with mandarin orange slices.
(I just decorate with oranges without extra Cool Whip.)
Delicious!

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Fry chicken tenders until golden brown.
Mix all ingredients. Serve while hot.

title: deviled potato salad
directions: Cut eggs in half; remove yolks and mash.
Blend with vinegar and mustard.
Add mayonnaise, sour cream and celery salt; mix well.
Chop egg whites; combine with potatoes and onions.
Fold in egg yolk mixture; chill.
Garnish with tomato wedges and cucumber slices.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large container.
Use 1/3 cup per 8 ounce mug of hot water.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups water with next 2 ingredients.
Add next 7 ingredients; pour over meat.
