Let marinate at least 3 hours. Drain.
Keep onion and 1 1/2 cups marinade.

title: holiday creambeets
directions: Cook all ingredients, then pour over beets.

title: chicken ritz
directions: Cook and cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top this with combined soup and sour cream mixture. Combine crumbs and poppy seed.
Sprinkle over cream mixture. Drizzle with margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: simple sloppy joes
directions: Cook meat and onions in a large skillet over medium heat until meat is browned and onion is tender; drain in a

colander and pat dry with a paper towel. Wipe pan drippings from skillet with a paper towel. Return beef mixture to skillet. Stir in remaining ingredients except hamburger bun. Cook until thoroughly heated. Spoon mixture evenly over bun halves. Yield: 2 servings.

title: pecan pie mini muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar, flour and pecans; set aside. Combine butter and eggs; mix well.
Stir into flour mixture just until moistened.
Fill greased and floured lined miniature muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes or until muffin test done.
Remove immediately to cool.
Yield about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mexican willies
directions: Mix together cream cheese, green chilies, green onions and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll and refrigerate overnight.
Slice.
Dip into salsa.

title: paula's western pot roast
directions: In large saucepot, brown on both sides meat in oil.
Add onion; cook until golden.
Combine catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and vinegar; pour over meat.
Simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 3 hours.
Serve sliced with sauce, along with carrot and potato chunks, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Sift and add last 4 ingredients.
Combine ingredients as listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites real stiff.
Continue beating, add brown sugar and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes.
Store in tight container when cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Marjoram is a mild cousin of oregano with a musky, mellow, almost nutty bouquet.
It is especially good with veal, lamb, poultry, potatoes and tomatoes.
Marjoram may be substituted for thyme or savory and may be an improvement over those herbs in many recipes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Pour grated zucchini in large bowl.
Add eggs, vegetable oil, sugar and vanilla.
Stir and set aside.
In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, then stir these ingredients into the squash and sugar mixture.
Add chopped nuts and raisins.
Lightly grease 2 loaf pans.
Pour an equal amount of batter into each pan.
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.
Let cool in the pan for about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and allow to completely cool.
Ready to serve, or freeze for later use.

title: mom's persimmon pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Check and lower heat for 15 more minutes.

title: yellow party punch
directions: Mix juices, lemonade mix and water the day before; refrigerate. The next day, add your sugar to taste.
Add ginger ale before serving.
Also a frozen ring of the juice of choice may be added before serving.

title: pecan praline cookies
directions: Place graham crackers in jelly-roll pan.
Boil butter and brown sugar exactly 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans.
Spread over cracker and bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: puerto rican
directions: Oil in heavy pan on medium heat.
Add garlic, onion, rice, corned beef and green pepper.

Stir about 2 minutes on high heat. Add 1 can Gondulas, 3 cups of water, Sazon, cilantro, tomato sauce and salt for five minutes then lower heat, cover lid with foil and place on pan, about 10 minutes; stir one time only, another 20 minutes done.
Serve with main dish.

title: mamma's wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Make a hole in center.
Add liquid ingredients; mix until smooth.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan or two 8-inch layer pans for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Pour pineapple with juice in 9-inch baking dish.
Crumble cake.
Mix over pineapple.
Put margarine over all.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 20 minutes until brown at 350°.
Use unsweetened fruit.

title: morcon (stuffed steak)
directions: Pound steak as thin as possible between wax paper.
Marinate in vinegar, mixed with garlic and black pepper for 30 minutes; reserve marinade.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate and oil in small saucepan over low heat. Cream butter until light; add sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add melted chocolate; mix well. Sift dry ingredients. Stir them into batter with the buttermilk. Mix zucchini and nuts into batter. Grease and flour two 9-inch pans or one big pan. Divide batter between pans or pour into big pan. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Cool before frosting.

title: green enchiladas
directions: In a blender, combine cilantro, jalapeno, salt, sugar, shortening, parsley and green salsa until very smooth.
Pour into a saucepan and heat on low.
In a separate bowl, combine the cooked chicken, Monterey Jack cheese, black olives and sour cream.
Set aside.
Heat the oil in a frying pan.
Dip a tortilla in the heated oil until soft and flexible, then in the heated salsa.
Fill with about 1/4 c. of the chicken mixture, roll and place in a baking dish.
Repeat until chicken mixture is gone.
Pour the excess salsa and cream over the enchiladas.
Top with green onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
If you freeze the enchiladas, wait to add the cream and green onions until you are ready to bake.

title: texas caviar(serves many)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Make at least one day in advance. Serve with chips. Can also be served over pasta.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Empty container of sherbet into punch bowl
Pour ginger ale over it and stir.

title: fred's "hole in one"
directions: Toast bread.
Cut out center of bread with biscuit cutter. Place circle aside.
Place toast in frying pan.
Drop egg in center of toast.
Fry as frying egg.
Salt and pepper to taste. Delicious!
Circle can be eaten with jelly, butter, cinnamon, etc.

title: microwave apple crisp
directions: Put apples in 8 or 9-inch round microwave dish.
Sprinkle juice or water over top.
If apples are sour, sprinkle several tablespoons sugar over top.
Melt butter.
Add to brown sugar, oatmeal, flour and cinnamon mixture.
Sprinkle over top. Microwave 8 minutes on High, rotating a half turn.
Microwave 6 to 8 more minutes on High or until apples are soft.
Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Dice chicken into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Saute chicken in butter and season with salt, pepper, chicken curry powder, paprika, oregano and chicken fry seasoning.
Dice onions, shred cheese and heat mushroom gravy mix according to instructions.
Mix chicken, cheese, onion and gravy mix together.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: May omit nuts and chips if you desire.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place in frying pan with butter over medium heat.
Cook one side for 10 minutes.
Turn breasts and add peppers and onions on top of chicken.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Then add Mozzarella cheese slices and cook, covered, until cheese is melted (at least 5 minutes).
Remove and serve.

title: "lasagna al kida"
directions: *Use the container you've got left from last week's spaghetti. If you don't have any, then, by all means go out and get some. It will then be left over from last week's lasagna.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cook kielbasa in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes, or brown it in a skillet.
Combine honey, mustard, jelly and pineapple in a large saucepan.
Add kielbasa; simmer over low heat for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
(It could be done ahead and reheated.)
Serve hot with toothpicks.
Makes a lot, about 6 cups. Leftover sauce could be used to glaze a ham.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to package.
When cake is done, punch holes in top and pour a can of cream of coconut on top.
Spread shredded coconut on top of cream of coconut.
Cool.

title: date cake
directions: Cook dates in water over low heat, stirring occasionally, until smooth and thick.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients together. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Stir in date mixture.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture (slow speed on mixer).
Stir in nuts.

title: pizza fruit pie
directions: Spread cookie mix on cookie sheet real thin.
Bake at 350° for about 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together; spread on cookie crust.
Put sliced fruit on top.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and put in roaster pan.
Combine remaining ingredients (except baking soda).
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Stir with a wooden spoon.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 10 minutes. Pour out on waxed paper.
Store in airtight container.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix cocoa and flour.
Add to creamed ingredients.
Alternate 1 cup buttermilk or sour milk. You can mix your own buttermilk using the powdered.
Dissolve baking soda in boiling water and add last. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: tuna rice pie
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cool.
Stir in beaten egg.
Spoon rice into buttered 1 1/2 quart baking dish. Press evenly on bottom and up sides to form a 1/2-inch wide rim. Combine soup and Worcestershire sauce in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into rice shell.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
(One 5 or 6 1/2-ounce can boned chicken or 1 cup diced cooked chicken may be substituted.)

title: chicken broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix chicken and broccoli with soup that is thinned with milk and broth.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots in 1-inch boiling water, until tender.
Drain and cool slightly.
In a large bowl, combine soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add carrots, stir gently to coat with dressing.
Add celery and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 6 cups.

title: dirt
directions: Crush up cookies.
Mix together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Mix together two mixtures.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Starting with Oreos, layer them and pudding mixture with Oreos on top.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter or oil.
Add egg and vanilla. Put dry ingredients all together in dish and add to zucchini and mix.
Add nuts and raisins.
Heat oven to 350°.
Drop cookie mix with teaspoon on cookie sheets, ungreased.
Bake about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 to 4 dozen.

title: large batch chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together and bake at 375°.

title: strawberry frosting
directions: Beat ingredients thoroughly.
Spread between layers and on top of 8-inch layers.
Yields enough frosting for two 8-inch layers.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Saute one-half to one pound ground beef and drain.
Prepare and set aside onion, Cheddar cheese and hot peppers.
Grease a large black iron skillet (or a large 9 x 13-inch casserole dish). Heat; sprinkle with corn meal or spray with Pam.
Pour one half of the batter into skillet, then add the hamburger, onion, pepper and cheese.
Then the other one-half of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Cut onions into thick slices.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.
Set aside.

title: taco casserole
directions: Ingredients vary due to size of casserole.

title: international coffee
directions: In heatproof container, mix cocoa mix and coffee.
Pour in boiling water; stir.
Top each serving with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat until very smooth.
Nuts may be sprinkled on top of filling.
Re-roll slowly and carefully.
Chill (can be frozen). You can sprinkle with powdered sugar.
I sometimes drizzle green colored icing over it and add chopped nuts to look like a Yule log.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine in baking pan.
Top with 3 or 4 strips bacon.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, reserving shells for shrimp broth. (May use chicken broth in place of shrimp broth.)
Place shells in a saucepan with 2 cups of water; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Strain broth; discard shells.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel
and
boil potatoes and onion until tender.
Spray casserole dish
with
Pam.	Pour
potatoes	and onion in dish. Add mushrooms,	drained, salt and pepper.
Add flour to margarine, then
milk.
When mixture thickens slightly add cheese. Pour this sauce over potatoes.
Heat in oven approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour a bundt pan. Mix by hand in large mixing bowl; oil, sugar and eggs. Add spices, baking soda and vanilla. Mix well and stir in flour, will be very stiff. Add apples and pecans. Bake 1 1/2 hours in 350 degree oven.

title: all-american cheesecake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in blender.
In a bowl, combine with 1/4 cup sugar and melted 1/4 cup sweet butter.
Press crumb mixture into bottom of spring-form pan.
In another bowl, combine cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar and blend.
Add one egg at a time, then add vanilla extract.
Mix until smooth.
Pour on top of crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown and firmly formed.
In a bowl combine sour cream and 1/3 cup sugar. Top onto cake and bake another 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool and refrigerate before serving.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Heat sugar, broth, vinegar, oil, soy sauce, salt and garlic to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, stirring occasionally.
Mix cornstarch and water; stir into sugar mixture. Cook and stir until thickened, about 10 seconds.
Stir in tomato, green pepper and pineapple.
Heat to boiling.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups sauce, 140 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: shrimp stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in margarine until golden brown.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, mushrooms and soup.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add sour cream just before serving over hot rice or noodles.
Garnish with chives.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: snow salad
directions: Mix dry jello with Cool Whip.
Mix in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Chill before serving.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls.
Separate each roll into 2 layers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spoon crab mixture on rolls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Whip ingredients together; let set 1/2 hour. On medium cookie sheet, place small pie tins. Put 1/4 cup hot oil in each pie tin. Spoon batter into pie tins. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch dish with hash browns. Brown onion with sausage.
Drain and spread over potatoes.
Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs and milk.
Season to taste.
Pour over mixture in dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: low cholesterol, fat-free bran muffins
directions: Beat the first 4 ingredients in blender until fluffy; set aside.
Blend dry ingredients with whisk.
Make well.
Add liquid ingredients, folding lightly with wooden spoon 20 minutes.
Put 1/2 batter in Teflon muffin tin or one sprayed with vegetable spray. Bake at 350°.
Turn out immediately onto board and upright to cool. Best served warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook until it thickens and boils. Pour into baked pie crust.

title: date roll
directions: Over medium-low heat, put sugar, butter and Pet milk in pan. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture forms soft ball in cold water. Add dates, stirring frequently, until candy thickens, bubbles, hiss and mixture follows spoon around pan.
Add pecans and coconut and continue cooking until mixture has consistency of soft cookie dough.
Pour in a long roll onto wet, cold lint-free cloth.
(Linen dish towel works good.)
Roll and let cool. Remove cloth and slice candy crosswise.

title: fruit nut squares
directions: Melt margarine. Cream sugar. Beat in eggs. Add flour and vanilla. Place nuts on bottom of greased 2 1/2-inch deep 8 x 13-inch pan. Pour batter over nuts. Cut candied cherries and pineapple. Place on top of batter. When done, cut in squares. Bake in 300° oven about 40 minutes. Makes about 12 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Drain off grease.
Add beans. Mix remaining ingredients together and stir into meat mixture. Bake in oblong baking dish at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Prepare 3-quarts plain popcorn.
Place in clean brown grocery sack.
Cook brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt on High for 2 minutes.
Stir.
Cook for another 2 minutes.
Add 1/2 tablespoon baking soda to mixture.
Stir.
Pour over popcorn in sack.
Shake bag.
Cook on High 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Cook another 1 1/2 minutes.
Shake.
Cool.

title: baked vidalia onion dip
directions: Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat; add onions and saut 10 minutes or until tender.
Stir together shredded Swiss cheese and next 5 ingredients; stir in onion, blending well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes and let stand 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.
Prep:
15 minutes.
Makes 6 cups.

title: carrot salad
directions: Recommended: electric Salad Shooter.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain grease off.
Put in crock-pot.
Add other ingredients; simmer.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in deep kettle; add seasoned salt.
Add crushed garlic and pepper.
Simmer 10 to 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Stir thoroughly, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse. Pour 1/3 of meat sauce into 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with strips of lasagna noodles.
Combine slightly beaten eggs, cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Arrange Mozzarella cheese over noodles, then egg mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Bake in 325` oven about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hermits
directions: Cream together the sugar and oil.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix and fold in raisins.
Blend this mixture with the dry ingredients; spread onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with confectioners sugar and cut into squares.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Prepare enchiladas:
In a large bowl, mix together diced chicken, diced cheese, 1/2 can diced tomatoes, half of the chopped onion, condensed soup and fresh herbs.
Spoon 1/8 of the mixture onto each tortilla and roll up, turning sides in if desired.
Place in a 9x13-inch baking pan.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan as soon as possible onto waxed paper that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll up and refrigerate for 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1 cup sugar, almond extract and lemon juice.
Heat in oven while preparing shortcake.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes seasoned with salt into baking dish.
Heat butter, flour, milk, cheese and pepper in a saucepan to make a sauce.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kal bi (korean bbq) marinade
directions: Combine ingredients and marinate beef strips for a few hours. Cook beef strips in a pan or barbecue on the grill.

title: south seas lime pie(yields 6 servings; pan size: 9-inch)
directions: Beat egg yolks in mixer bowl until thick and lemon-colored. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, lime juice, lime rind and food coloring.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar in bowl until stiff, but not dry.
Fold gently into lime mixture.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with cookie crumbs.
Microwave on Low for 25 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean, turning dish 1/2 turn halfway through cooking time.
Cool.

title: gingered ambrosia
directions: Peel and section oranges over a bowl, reserving juice. Combine orange sections, juice and remaining ingredients; toss gently. Cover and chill until ready to serve. Garnish, if desired.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Combine the cream cheese and mayonnaise and mix well. Add the pepper and liquid from the olives and mix. Fold in the pecans and chopped olives. Serve on crackers or as a spread for sandwiches.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat well.
Pour in large tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake is done.

title: traveling tortilla
directions: On a large plate, layer ingredients.
Decorate plate with tortilla chips.
There won't be any leftovers.

title: glazed carrots(rabbits aren't the only ones who like carrots.)
directions: Clean and slice carrots.
Cook in pan of boiling water until tender, then place in a serving dish.
In a separate saucepan, blend sugar, flour, bacon, fat, vinegar and water; cook 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Mix well. Pour over hot cooked carrots and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: graham cracker crunch
directions: Mix butter, sugar and pecans. Boil for 5 minutes on medium. Spread graham crackers over large cookie sheet. Then pour mixture over crackers and bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Let cool and then break into pieces.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Grease 9-inch or 10-inch pie pan.
Pour in batter.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Place in mixing bowl.
Add chopped onion, Worcestershire sauce and small amount of Tabasco sauce.
Beat with electric mixer until completely blended.
Chill until workable.
Sprinkle paprika and chopped nuts on waxed paper. Shape cheese into ball and roll well on waxed paper.
Chill.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Turn oven on broil.
Mix ground beef, egg, salt and pepper. Form into ball about size of a soft ball.
Wrap a piece of uncooked bacon around the ball and pat down to make a stick steak. Place in oven broiler.
Cook 15 minutes on each side.
Do not puncture meat.
Keep juices inside.
Cook onions in frying pan with butter.
Pour over cooked meat.

title: three cheese chicken bake
directions: Cook lasagna noodles.
Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in soup, pimento, mushrooms and milk.
Layer 1/2 of the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or glass dish; top with 1/2 of the cottage cheese, 1/2 of the soup mixture, 1/2 of chicken and 1/2 of American cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Then top with remaining American cheese and Parmesan.
Bake 2 minutes more and eat!

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together; set aside.
Mix cake mix, 3 eggs and apple pie filling together.
Pour 1/2 of cake mixture into a cake pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with 1/2 the cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Top with the remaining cake mixture and sprinkle with remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: snack crackers
directions: Line 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil and line with crackers.
Spread almonds over crackers.
In saucepan, melt butter and add sugar, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pour evenly over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned.
Remove from oven and cool.
While still slightly warm, break into squares.

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix 1 cup granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Dip each biscuit piece in mixture and drop into well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Mix 1/2 cup granulated sugar and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Pour over top.
Cut 1 stick oleo in pieces and lay around top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and serve with club crackers.
This is real good.

title: zucchini potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broth and heat to boiling.
Remove from heat and beat in 1/4 cup potatoes (add more, if needed to thicken mixture), salt, pepper and parsley.
Beat in milk.
Add zucchini.
Simmer and stir for 15 minutes.

title: easy potato cheese soup
directions: I use the microwave oven.
Cook onion with paprika in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: rocky road
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Take off heat and mix in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread in pan and let set for 1/2 hour. Cut into squares.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Lightly beat eggs together.
Add mayonnaise and water and scramble lightly.
Heat large skillet on medium-low; add margarine. Add egg mixture.
When eggs are set on the edges, stir slightly. Repeat whenever edges are set.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Do not overcook.
Serves 4.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Put in chicken and pour butter over.
Combine flour, milk and baking powder; then spread over chicken.
Combine broth and celery soup. Pour over top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until smooth.
Add pimiento, bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into ball or logs and roll in nuts.

title: granny's lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients at once and pour into ready-made pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Real lemony!!!!!)

title: venison meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs; add tomato sauce, onion, crumbs, salt and pepper. Add venison and mix well. Press into an ungreased loaf pan.

title: banana bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and bananas, beating until light. Alternately add flour mixture and milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: easy italian stir-fry for pasta
directions: Drain the juice from the 2 cans of tomatoes into a large frying pan.
Cook the peppers, onions and spices in the juice for about 10 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, cover and cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Spoon over cooked pasta.

title: cavatini
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sherried beef
directions: Mix all together; cook on low in crock-pot all day.
Serve over wide noodles.
Delicious.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Pour in cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Pat dry cake mix evenly over the top, then evenly pour butter on top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut the bread and spread on bottom of pan.
Brown sausage.
Drain and sprinkle over bread cubes. Cover with grated Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, 2 1/2 cups milk and dry mustard.
Pour over the bread, sausage and cheese in pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, mix the cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Pour on top of mixture and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fresh corn salad with tomato vinaigrette
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the rice, corn, celery and shallot. In a blender or food processor, combine the tomato, lemon juice, vinegar, basil, thyme, mustard, salt and pepper.
Process on high until well combined (about 25 seconds).
Pour the dressing over the salad and toss about 30 times to coat well.
Serve over the romaine leaves at room temperature or very slightly chilled for a lunch or dinner entre.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mary's orange salad
directions: Chill until mushy.
Combine Dream Whip and Jell-O.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients, using 1/2 of Eagle Brand milk and pour 1/2 of batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressing, mayonnaise and cheese. Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Slice onion and green pepper.
Slice potatoes.
Fry chops in oil until almost cooked.
Arrange chops, onion, pepper and potatoes in casserole dish.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Coat skillet with cooking spray.
Add chicken pieces and cook thoroughly.
Add teriyaki sauce, onions, and peppers.
Cover and cook on low-medium 5-10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with a little water, and stir thoroughly. Add to chicken in skillet, and simmer on medium 10 minutes, or until sauce is thickened.
Serve over cooked white rice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients and place in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: never fail souffle breakfast meal
directions: Cut bread into cubes.
Place tight in buttered 10 x 12-inch dish oblong.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften the cream cheese with juice from 1 can of clams.
Drain juice from other 2 cans of clams and set aside.
Discard juice. Add minced onion, clams, garlic, Tabasco sauce, and Worcestershire sauce to softened cream cheese.
Blend in mixer or by hand.
Chill and serve or serve immediately.

title: orzo con parmesan
directions: Saute orzo in butter until browned lightly.
Add chicken broth; simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add fresh grated Parmesan cheese and chopped basil.

title: oyster stuffing
directions: Mix the oysters well with the bread crumbs and seasoning; add the melted fat.

title: butter rolls
directions: Roll out biscuit dough thin.
Cut into squares.
Spread with soft margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar, covering margarine.
Roll dough up; place rolls in skillet.
Bake until done.
Mix milk with sugar and vanilla; pour over rolls while still hot in skillet.

title: peanut butter chocolate kisses cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, peanut butter and butter in mixing bowl. Beat until thoroughly blended.
Add egg and vanilla; blend well. Add flour and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate for about 1 hour.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Put raisins and water in medium saucepan.
Cook until water is absorbed.
Combine applesauce and baking soda.
Mix well.
Mix flour, Sweet 'N Low, honey, oil, cinnamon, eggs, nuts and chopped apple.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In a large bowl, combine milk, Bisquick, sausage and Cheez Whiz and blend well. Roll into 1-inch balls.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut 8 to 10 slices of white bread into small pieces and put into pan.

Grate cheese on top of bread. Brown sausages and cut into pieces and place on top of cheese. Mix together eggs, mustard, 2 cups milk, pepper and salt to taste. Pour mixture over bread, cheese and sausage layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Just before baking, put on mushrooms and pour mixture of soup and 1/2 cup milk over all.
Bake 1 hour uncovered, at 350°.
It's delicious.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Preheat oven to 375°. In a greased skillet, bake until brown.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
In a large Dutch oven, cover beans with water and soak for 8 hours.
Drain.
Coat a large Dutch oven with cooking spray; place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add celery and next 4 ingredients.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except rice and cook, uncovered, over medium heat 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves; serve over rice. Start rice mid-way through cooking.
Makes 9 servings.
May substitute 1 pound sliced smoked sausage for ham.

title: oriental salad
directions: Mix oil, sugar, vinegar. Toss together all other ingredients, then pour oil mixture over and serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add Sloppy Joe sauce and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Place cheese on bun and add portion of Sloppy Joe/hamburger mixture and heat in oven until cheese melts.

title: special chicken
directions: Place chicken in Tupperware container. Cover with Italian dressing.
Let soak all day or overnight.
Grill or broil on low until done.

title: winter compote
directions: Place all ingredients in a baking dish; cover and bake for 1 hour or until pears are tender.
Chill before serving.
Delicious! Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all ingredients except soup; form into balls. Put soup and 1 soup can of water into pressure cooker and stir. Drop meatballs into soup. Pressure cook for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry nut cake
directions: Mix the ingredients in mixer.
Grease three 8-inch round pans. Pour batter in 3 pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. When layers are cool, make icing and ice between layers and all over cake.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Top with onions.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Remove bones from chicken.
Place back into juice that it cooked in.
Add 1 can chicken broth.
Flatten biscuits out and cut into small squares.
Put biscuit squares into hot broth.
Cook until tender.

title: wild blueberry ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: "say more" franks
directions: In small saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except frankfurters, and simmer, uncovered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 400°. Place frankfurters single layer in a lightly greased casserole dish and pour sauce over them.
Bake 20 minutes, basting franks occasionally.
Spoon sauce over frankfurters to serve.

title: hearty biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all dry ingredients. Add buttermilk and oil to dry ingredients with the yeast.
Mix well. Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Take out as much as needed
to make
biscuits.
Knead, roll, cut and bake.
(Will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator.)

title: sausage casserole
directions: Combine soup mix, rice and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Crumble and sear sausage in skillet.
Add onion, celery, mushrooms and almonds.
Mix with soup mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in ungreased casserole.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat sugar, corn syrup, water and salt to boiling, stirring frequently until sugar is dissolved.

Stir in peanuts. Carefully set candy thermometer in place and continue to cook, stirring frequently until temperature reaches 300° or hard crack stage (when a small amount of mixture dropped into a bowl of very cold water separates into hard and brittle threads), about 20 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat; immediately stir in butter or margarine and baking soda.

title: ratatouille
directions: Sprinkle eggplant with salt and let drain in colander for about one hour.
Rinse, drain and pat dry.
Set aside.
Saute the onion, squash and garlic in olive oil until slightly soft to the touch.
Add in the tomatoes and eggplant.
Saute until eggplant is soft.
Season to taste with herbs and spices.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Cover with layer of cheese followed by a layer of bread crumbs.
Drizzle with melted butter and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: hot tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion and peppers.
Add soups.
Mix well. Line bottom of baking dish with tortillas and sliced cheese.
Add half of meat mixture.
Add another layer of tortillas and cheese. Add remaining meat mixture.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil in 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs, all at once.
Continue beating until smooth.
Drop dough by scant 1/4 cupfuls about 3 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until puffed and golden 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool away from draft.
Cut off tops; pull out any filaments of soft dough.
Beat whipping cream with sugar and vanilla in chilled mixing bowl until stiff; fill puffs.
Replace tops.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes 12 cream puffs.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan good with oleo and lightly flour. Spread even 2 cups chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Mix 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 1 stick oleo, 1 cup unsifted plain flour and 2 well beaten eggs.
Spread on pecans.
Take 1/2 pound red cherries and 1/2 pineapple and spread on batter.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Fry sausage and drain well.
Mix remaining ingredients. Add crumbled sausage to biscuit dough.
Roll dough on floured surface and cut with biscuit cutter.
Cook at 400° until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well and add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and salt; add to egg mixture.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: dessert shells
directions: With drinking glass or cookie cutter, cut one circle from each slice of bread.
Spread both sides of bread with butter and press each into a muffin tin or custard dishes.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon in each bread shell and place in preheated 375° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until the shells are golden brown.
Remove the shells from the pan and allow to cool.
Fill each shell with drained fruit, jello or fresh fruit (strawberries, kiwi, cantaloupe, etc.) and top with whipped cream if desired.
Enjoy.

title: almond cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, milk, salt and almond extract; beat well.
Stir in flour.
Chill until firm.
When chilled, form into 1-inch balls.
Dip in egg white and roll in almonds.
Place each ball on cookie sheet.
Press a cherry half in center of each cookie.
Bake in oven at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
This mixture may be frozen before cooking up to one month.

title: lima beef soup
directions: Combine the first seven ingredients and simmer for 2 hours. Add mixed vegetables, lima beans, noodles and pepper.
Simmer 1 to 2 hours longer.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and marshmallows.
Pour in an 8-inch square pan.
Cream the butter and 3/4 cup sugar and add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour batter over fruit. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: best bread in the world
directions: Pour the boiling water over the old fashioned rolled oats. Let stand until thoroughly softened.
Soak yeast in lukewarm water.
It must not be too hot.
You can test it by dropping a little on your wrist.
Add the salt, honey and melted butter, cooled to lukewarm to the oats.
Making sure that the oats are just lukewarm, add the yeast and mix well.
Gradually add the flours and knead with your hands until the dough is smooth and elastic.
This should take approximately 10 minutes.
Pour into a lightly oiled bowl, turning it around to coat the dough on all sides.

title: swedish coffee treat
directions: Mix together and store in an airtight jar with lid.
Add one heaping teaspoon to 1 cup of freshly brewed coffee and a slice of orange.

title: scampi georgio
directions: Heat the butter and oil in a saute pan.
Add garlic and onions and saute until golden.
Do not let the garlic burn as it will tend to caramelize.
Add the wine and deglaze the pan.
Now, add the parsley, basil and oregano.
Simmer until wine has reduced almost completely.
Add salt and peppers; check taste.
Now, add the shrimp and lemon juice; toss until shrimp are pink and tender. Serve over al dente capaldoni.

title: rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole; mix thoroughly.
Place casserole in baking pan with about 1-inch hot water.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Serve warm chilled with or without cream.

title: perked hot cider
directions: Place candies, orange, cinnamon and clove in percolator basket.
Perk and enjoy!
Cider becomes very hot, so unplug when finished perking.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix noodles, hamburger and sauces together.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 2 cups of shredded cheese over mixture. Top with pepperoni.
Cook in microwave oven for 15 minutes or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot-orange punch
directions: Add sugar to hot tea and stir to dissolve sugar.
Allow to cool.
Add remaining ingredients with ginger ale added just prior to
serving.
Add ice if desired.
Yields approximately 26 (4 ounce) punch cupfuls.

title: coconut shrimp
directions: Mix cold water (2/3 cup) and 2 tablespoons of curry powder. Peel shrimp and add to water mixture.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Sear meat with onion.
Mix with cornbread mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: corn bread
directions: Prepare Jiffy corn bread mix as directed.
Set aside. Do the same with yellow cake mix.
Mix the two batters together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: canned hamburger meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Form meatballs and pack in jars.
Cold pack 3 hours.
Pressure can 90 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: apricot cobble-up
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients except apricot halves and ice cream with fork to a soft dough.
Spread in 8 x 8 x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Pour apricots with syrup over batter.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: In medium saucepan, mix chili and cream cheese over medium heat.
Serve when cheese is melted.
Best warm with tortilla chips.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can onions.
Pour in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until onions are brown.

title: potato and fri chik salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Dice eggs and potatoes.
Season to taste with salt, pepper and onion.
May add whatever seasonings you desire.
Add mayonnaise and diced Fri Chik and toss.

title: brownie sheet cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Boil butter, cocoa and water. Add to flour and sugar mixture; mix with mixer. Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla. Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix butter, syrup, sugar, eggs and flavoring.
Add pecans. Place pastry in muffin tins and pour in pie mixture. Bake in slow oven until set.

title: coffee tortoni
directions: Toast coconut and chopped almonds.
Whip egg white with coffee; gradually add 2 teaspoons sugar.
Whip cream; add remaining sugar, vanilla and almond extract.
Fold cream into egg mixture; add coconut and almonds.
Pour into fluted paper baking cups.
Sprinkle with additional coconut, if desired.
Freeze 2 hours or more.
Serves 6.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Spread uncooked rice into bottom of dish.
Place pork chops on rice.
Pour soup over pork chops. Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, milk, egg and 1 cup crumbs.
Put into a greased casserole and sprinkle with buttered crumbs made with 1/2 cup crumbs in the melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.

title: barbecue kielbasa
directions: Slice kielbasa into 1/4-inch rings and pan-fry with small amount of water until slightly brown; warm through.
Add desired amount of barbecue sauce and heat.
Remove from stove and serve.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until soft in 1 tablespoon oil; add cumin and chili powder.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Brown chicken breasts in small amount of cooking oil and arrange in baking dish.

title: salsa
directions: Medium chop, yellow, poblano and cubanita peppers; de-seed and fine grate jalapeno and scotch bonnet pepper (if very hot salsa is desired, do not de-seed). Peel, de-seed and fine chop tomatoes. In large bowl mix pepper, tomatoes, garlic, herbs and juice of 1 lemon. Add salt and pepper; refrigerate 1/2 hour. Toss again and add oil and lemon juice. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: french toast
directions: Lightly oil non-stick pan and heat on medium.
Lightly beat egg and applesauce by hand.
Soak each slice of bread on both sides.
Brown bread in skillet on both sides, top with strawberry jam.
Serves two.
Calories:
100 (1 slice).
Fat:
1 gm., 9% fat.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour in pan.
Add milk and stir, then add eggs and margarine.
Cook over low heat until thick.
When ready to eat, put graham crackers on bottom of dessert dish, then bananas and pudding on top.

title: lentils with vegetables
directions: Rinse lentils in colander with cold water; set aside to drain. Chop onion; set aside.
Peel carrots, chop celery, wash and chop potatoes (leave skin on).
Set aside.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.

Grease a 10 x 1 1/2-inch pie plate. Sprinkle turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into plate.

title: hamburger on a bun
directions: Combine all ingredients except buns.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide mixture into 6 equal portions.
Put mixture on buns and shape with thumbs so that meat completely covers bottom half of bun.
Place on cookie sheet and cook 3-inches from top unit with oven control on broil at 350°.
Cook for 10 to 12 minutes or until meat is gray and juice bubbles on top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, or butter, and sugar in large mixing bowl. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Add flour and flavoring, mixing well. Pour into a greased tube or bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; test for doneness.
Can put pats of butter or margarine on top after removing from the oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Spread the nuts in the bottom of the pie shell.
Pour in the filling.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini and tomato casserole
directions: Make sauce:
Saute onion and garlic until golden in butter and oil about 5 minutes; add salt, basil, pepper and tomato sauce. Bring to boiling and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Cut lettuce very small.
Add onion.
Add vinegar and salt to taste.
Heat bacon grease until smoking.
Pour over lettuce (amount to taste), then toss.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Thoroughly
cream
margarine,
sugar
and cream cheese. Add eggs,
one	at
a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour
and add to creamed mixture.	Add vanilla extract. Bake in 9-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add 1/2 stick butter (melted), Tabasco, salt and cream cheese.
Sprinkle herb dressing and 1/2 stick melted butter over top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Sift flour once.
Mix all the ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Make small dent in cookie ball with the end of a chopstick or ice pick dipped in red food color.
Handle the dough very carefully.
This is a very short dough.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: sesame baked chicken
directions: Wash chicken and place in a shallow dish.
Pour buttermilk over and cover tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, pour off buttermilk and pat chickens dry with paper towels.
Melt butter with tarragon.
Add lemon juice.
Mix bread crumbs, parsley, sesame seed and seasoned salt well.
Dip chicken pieces in butter, then roll in crumbs to coat thoroughly.
Arrange chicken on a baking tray.
Spoon remaining butter over all the pieces.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until about 1 1/2 hours before dinner.
Bake chicken in a moderate oven, 350°, without turning, until chicken is golden and fork-tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally with drippings.
To serve, arrange chickens on a large platter and garnish with parsley and radish roses.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk together and bring to a boil. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Spoon onto wax paper in cluster as large or small as you prefer.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion (chopped) in vegetable oil.
Add tomatoes, steak sauce, catsup, green pepper (chopped) and parsley. In the meantime, cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain macaroni and mix with hamburger mixture.
Stir in mushroom soup. Put in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles.
You can freeze one.
Add cheese and bake after it is completely thawed.

title: roast beef with garlic-basil puree
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan.
Add garlic. Cover, reduce heat to medium-high and cook 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Peel garlic.
Combine garlic, basil and salt in food processor; process until smooth.
Set aside.
Trim excess fat from roast.
Rub garlic puree over entire surface of meat.
Coat rack of a broiler pan with cooking spray.
Place roast on rack.
Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of roast.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until meat thermometer registers 140° (rare) or 160° (medium).

title: creole pralines
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, water and Karo until syrup makes a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
Add pecans.
Cook until syrup forms a hard ball in cold water.
Drop by spoonfuls onto corn shucks.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat a small pressure cooker or saucepan. Melt shortening and brown meat. Add 1/2 cup of water (more if you are using saucepan). Cook meat until tender. Add vegetables and cook until they are tender. Season with salt and pepper. Thicken with balance of water and flour, mixed together. This makes a hearty meal served with cornbread and a green salad.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef and onion.
Add taco mix and green chilies.
Layer beans, meat, cheese and taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: potato salad allemand
directions: Fry the bacon in a skillet until crisp, then remove from skillet.
Brown the onion in bacon drippings.
Add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Add potatoes and parsley and heat thoroughly.
Place in a serving bowl and sprinkle with bacon.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable pilaf
directions: Combine rice, soups, cheese and pimiento; stir well and set aside.
Combine spinach, broccoli and 1 cup French fried onions. Spread 1/2 cooked rice mixture in 8 x 12-inch dish.
Top with vegetable mixture, then rest of rice mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.
tags: cream of mushroom and cream of celery soup

title: fruit dip
directions: Add all ingredients to bowl.
Beat until thickened. Refrigerate.
Serve with strawberries, banana, pineapple, pears and mandarin oranges.
Always a hit at parties.

title: parsley potato pancakes
directions: Squeeze the grated potatoes in a towel until fairly dry.
Mix with the eggs, flour, onion, salt and parsley.
Heat a heavy pan or griddle.
Add a light coating of oil.
Ladle on the mixture and form pancakes.
Cook until brown.
Turn and cook on the other side (about 4 to 6 minutes a side).
Garnish with sour cream.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: avocado, pear and pineapple salad(serves 2 to 4)
directions: Optional:
Add tuna, nuts or cottage cheese for a more substantial meal.
Pears can substitute for part or all of pineapple.

title: s'mores cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine graham cracker crumbs, flour, sugar, and butter.
Beat at low speed scraping bowl until mixture resembles small peas.
Reserve 1 1/4 cup for topping. Press remaining mixture in a 9 inch square pan.

title: south texas chicken
directions: Pour chicken broth in skillet and heat.
Dip tortillas in broth until soft.
Place tortillas in bottom of oblong baking dish and around edges.
Mix all other ingredients together in bowl and then pour in baking dish over tortillas.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: cornish hen with parsley sauce
directions: Wash and dry chicken thoroughly.
Combine flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Shake chicken pieces in flour mixture to coat evenly.
Melt butter in a heavy skillet with cover or a Dutch oven.
Stir in marjoram, thyme, sage, chili powder and paprika. When butter is bubbly, add chicken pieces, a few at a time, brown evenly on all sides.

title: chicken squares
directions: Mix together cream cheese, 4 tablespoons butter, chicken, salt, pepper, milk and chives.
Divide into 8 portions.
Separate each can of crescent rolls into 4 sections, making 8 squares.
Put chicken mixture in center and pull up corners to make square, closing and pinching all seams.
Brush top of squares with remaining 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle crushed croutons on top.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown in preheated 375° oven. Serves 8.

title: christmas breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in pan.
Add sausage and cheese.
Beat eggs with mustard.
Pour over bread.
Pour milk over all.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Excellent souffle!

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Melt shortening.
In large bowl, beat egg, sugar and salt.
Add warm melted shortening, water and flour.
Then add yeast mixture.
Mix good with spoon.
Butter or grease batter and let rise in bowl. Let rise about double the size.
After it rises, sift enough flour on top to make it easy to make the rolls.
To make rolls, just pinch off enough dough to make a roll and put them in a greased pan and put melted butter on top.
You may refrigerate leftover dough.

title: herb dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Taste for seasoning.
Refrigerate until serving time.
Makes a little over a cup of dip.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with coloring and cocoa.
Add vinegar and milk.
Sift salt, flour and soda.
Add to mixture by blending (do not beat).
After flour is added, add vanilla.
Grease two 9-inch pans.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven. Cool and split layers, using thread.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the marshmallow cream and add the Cool Whip.
Blend.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain and cool to room temperature.
Cut lettuce, add tomatoes, onions and cheese. Drain kidney beans and olives.
Add to salad.
Add 1000 Island dressing to hot sauce to salad.
Stir.
Just before serving add chips and cool hamburger.
Stir.

title: jelled peach sauce
directions: Drain syrup from peaches; set aside.
Puree peaches in blender.
To syrup, add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add sugar and nutmeg to liquid and boil for 1 minute.
Empty jello into bowl and stir in hot liquid until jello is dissolved, then add peaches. Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: baked pork chop casserole
directions: Spread rice over bottom of buttered casserole.
Spread mushrooms over, then 1/2 soup mix.
Brown pork chops and add.
Add rest of soup mix and hot liquid.
Seal casserole with aluminum foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Add more liquid, if needed.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Brown roast on high temperature. Put roast along with the rest of ingredients in slow cooker. Let simmer 8 hours. Serve on sandwich rolls with Swiss cheese.

title: char's maraschino cherry cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add shortening, cherry juice, cherries (cut in eighths) and milk. Beat.
Add egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Slice angel food cake into 2 layers.
Prepare Dream Whip per package instructions, then add remaining ingredients to Dream Whip.
Frost cake between layers and over sides and top.
Use pie filling to fill holes and around sides of cake.
Refrigerate cake.

title: apricot plytsok with meringue nut topping
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, butter, sour cream, sugar and baking powder, lemon peel and egg yolks together.
Divide dough almost in half.
Refrigerate dough 1 to 2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil broccoli in small amount of water until tender, but still bright green.
Mix with rice and undiluted soup.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle thin layer of bread crumbs on top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: turkey crunch(microwave)
directions: Combine margarine, celery, onion and green pepper in a 2-quart microwave-safe covered casserole dish.

Cook on High , covered, 5 minutes or until tender, stirring once during cooking time. Combine soup and milk in a small bowl; stir into onion mixture. Stir in 2 cups chow mein noodles (1/2 can), cooked turkey, mushrooms, green beans, pimento, poultry seasoning and salt.
Cook on High 7 to 8 minutes.
Stir once.
Sprinkle remaining noodles around edge of casserole.
Cook on High for 30 seconds.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Microwaves vary, make sure it is hot enough.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash shrimp.
In a large pan, melt the butter; add pepper and dressing.
Add shrimp, stirring to cover good.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Peel and enjoy.
Use bread to dip in butter-dressing mixture.

title: quick-n-easy taco salad
directions: Cook beef, onion and taco seasoning until brown; drain and cool.
Toss lettuce and tomatoes and cooled meat.
Add cheese and crushed Doritos just prior to serving.
Use enough dressing to make salad moist.
Serves 6 to 8 as main meal, 10 to 12 as side dish. May add kidney beans, pinto beans or any other flavored beans to stretch the meal.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually, beating well. Blend in shortening.
Stir dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut and fry in deep hot fat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Remove skin and bone from chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Place in casserole dish; set aside.

title: chicken, rice and vegetable medley
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat from bones.
Reserve broth.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch, 2-quart baking dish or 9-inch square pan.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 (1-cup) servings.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound out chicken with mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Mix next 4 ingredients together.
Combine this mixture with 1 tablespoon butter in the center of each chicken breast.
Rub into chicken breasts; roll and secure with toothpicks.
Put chicken in flour, then eggs and then bread crumbs.
Deep fry for 7 minutes at 325° or until golden brown or place chicken, seam side down in greased pan.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add cornflakes. Stir well.
Will be very thick and hard to stir.
Pour out; cut into squares while warm.
Don't press too hard.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Blend together and chill for 2 hours.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an 8-inch pan.
Mix well, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Combine this mixture with milk.
Pour this mixture over the melted butter.
Pour fruit over the dough and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
In a glass dish, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Drain pineapple and peaches.
Cut peaches into pieces.
Put jello in Cool Whip; mix well, then add cottage cheese and fruit. Mix well.
May add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Toss cabbage, onion and sugar.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
In small saucepan, mix vinegar, salt, celery seed and mustard seed. Bring to a boil, add salad oil and boil 1 minute.
Let cool 2 to 3 minutes, then pour over cabbage.
Toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss occasionally to mix.
Serves 6.

title: banana pie
directions: Blend and cook in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hot dog appetizers
directions: Cut hot dog in thirds; wrap bacon around hot dog and secure with a toothpick.
Sprinkle the brown sugar over all. Bake 1/2 hour, covered; bake 1/2 hour, uncovered at 350°.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, egg, catsup and salt, if desired (1 tablespoon) in bowl.
Mix well. Combine sauerkraut, cheese, pastrami, sour cream and mustard.
Place 1/3 of meat mixture in loaf pan.
Spread with sauerkraut mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with meat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: betty jane salad
directions: Use over spinach greens, lettuce, bean sprouts and hard boiled eggs.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, zucchini, sugar, oil and vanilla; set aside.
Mix together flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nuts and coconut.
Blend with egg mixture and bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 loaves or 1 loaf and 3 little loaves.
Bake the 3 little loaves for around 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes about 6 dozen muffins.
Bake them for 15 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Boil water, butter and cocoa, then pour over the flour mixture. Beat eggs, oil, buttermilk, soda and vanilla together. Add to mix. Pour in cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tamales and noodles
directions: Brown green pepper and onion.
Grease a casserole or baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut into small pieces.
Prepare rotini per package directions; drain.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening over low heat; remove from heat.
Blend in sugar.
Cool.
Stir in eggs.
Measure flour by dip/level or by sifting.
Blend flour, baking powder and salt; mix well in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in well-greased square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Makes about 18 bars.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese following package directions; mix in large bowl.
Then add the next 6 ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, marshmallows, 1 tablespoon butter, salt and pepper.
Shape into 12 balls.
Place in baking dish. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Combine honey
and 1 tablespoon butter; heat.
Using two forks, roll each ball in honey mixture, then in nuts.
Return to baking dish.
Spoon 2 tablespoons butter over each ball.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: sara's pasta salad
directions: Mix all and chill. A bag of frozen vegetables and corkscrew macaroni can be substituted.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Make a double crust recipe of pie pastry.
Roll it all out at once to 18-inch width and cut into 6-inch squares.
Toss blackberries in sugar and flour.
Place a mound onto the center of each square.
Place a chunk of butter in the center and fold the corners of the dough to the center, pinching edges of pastry together.
Put the dumplings close together in a greased baking pan.

title: potato soup with dill
directions: Melt butter over medium heat. Add carrots, leeks, garlic and potatoes. Saut, stirring constantly 4 minutes. Add dill, stock and milk and stir to mix. Bring mixture to simmer, then reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat and transfer 3/4 of soup to food processor or blender. Process to puree and return to pan and season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: beef stew 57
directions: Sprinkle beef with salt, pepper and sugar.
Brown in Crisco. Mix bouillon cubes in water.
Add to beef.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add 57 sauce and vegetables; simmer for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Thicken broth with a small amount of flour and water mixture.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix together eggs, milk and sugar.
Boil until slightly thick. Add remaining ingredients and freeze.

title: walnut cornbread stuffing
directions: Bake cornbread and cool.
Saute onions, celery and butter until onions are clear.
Combine stuffing mix, cornbread, salt, pepper, sage, walnuts, celery and onion mixture and eggs.
Add broth until mixture is moist.
You may add turkey broth instead of chicken.
Stir mixture thoroughly.
Bake at 500° for 30 minutes. This stuffing bakes wonderfully in a cast-iron pan.
For best results, preheat you pan and coat with spraying oil (Pam).

title: spicy frankfurters
directions: Cut the franks in half.
Place in a deep skillet.
Combine the flour with the 3 tablespoons water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour the sauce over the franks.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Then add to peanut butter mixture.
Add chocolate chips last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and bone.
Pull chicken from bone.
Using broth from chicken, mix Pepperidge Farm cornbread dressing.
Set aside. Mix soup and milk together; set aside.
In 10 x 13-inch baking dish, put layer of chicken, then a layer of soup.
Place dressing on top.
Bake at 350° until gravy bubbles.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Saut onions, garlic, mushrooms, carrots and peppers until soft. Add tomatoes, parsley, basil, oregano, chili powder, rosemary and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes. Mix together the 3 cheeses. Starting with sauce, layer with 8 cooked lasagna noodles and cheese in an 8 x 12-inch casserole. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: rice pudding in a crock-pot
directions: On stove, cook rice in water until water is evaporated.

title: pretzel salad(a dessert salad)
directions: Mix together pretzels, oleo and sugar.
Reserve 1 cup for top. Put remaining crumbs in a 9 x 13-inch pan and reserve crumbs in another pan.
Bake both for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip and sugar.
Spread on cooled pretzel layer. Dissolve jello in boiling water; add berries and chill until partially set.
Pour over cream cheese layer; chill.
Sprinkle with remaining pretzel crumbs when ready to serve.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour half the cake batter into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: heka
directions: Pour 3/4 cup peanut oil in a large pan (electric deep-fryer). Brown steak that has been cut in 2 1/2 inch diagonal strips.
Add soy sauce and sugar.
Simmer until time to add vegetables.
About 40 minutes before serving time, add in this order: (all vegetables are cut in 2-3 inch strips) Carrots - 40 minutes, Celery - 25 minutes, Green Pepper - 15 minutes, Green Onions - 5 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Separate eggs.
Melt chocolate and butter together.
Mix egg yolks and sugar.
Cool chocolate and butter.
Add to eggs and sugar alternately with flour.
Add vanilla and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and nuts.
Bake in greased and floured pan 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: white chip orange dream cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl. Beat butter, granulated sugar and brown sugar in large mixing bowl until creamy. Beat in egg and orange peel. Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in morsels. Drop dough by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Let stand for 2 minutes, then take up.

title: colorado cache best oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine eggs, raisins and vanilla.
Cover with plastic wrap. Let stand 1 hour.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add flour, cinnamon and soda to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Blend in egg raisin mixture and oatmeal.
Dough will be stiff.
Drop by heaping teaspoons onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. The secret is soaking the raisins.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except zucchini.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Spread evenly in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dana's cheddar cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the butter or margarine. Add the carrots, onion, green pepper and celery. Cook and stir over medium-low heat until the vegetables are tender. Sprinkle the vegetables with the flour, adding it 1 tablespoon at a time, stirring until the flour is blended in. Add the chicken broth to the saucepan. Cook and stir over medium heat until the mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat; add the shredded Cheddar cheese, stirring with a large whisk until the cheese is melted. Slowly add evaporated milk, stirring until the mixture is well blended and heated through. Add enough freshly ground pepper to taste. If desired, add several drops of bottled hot sauce and garnish with sunflower seeds. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all vegetables together.
Blend cheese and mayonnaise together and mix with vegetables.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cherry crunch cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt. Blend butter and sugar; add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in syrup and add dry ingredients. Mix well.
Spoon out cookie batter and roll in crushed corn flake crumbs. Place on greased baking sheet. Press 1/4 of cherry lightly
into top of each cookie and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast, hot water and sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add the oil, buttermilk and soda.
Stir; add the flour.
Mix well. Chill in refrigerator 2 hours or overnight, covered.
Take amount necessary and roll out on floured board. Bake at 400° until browned.
Dough will keep at least 1 week in refrigerator.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Boil water and raisins for 5 minutes.
Cool, then add vanilla and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and blend. Stir in dry ingredients, then add raisin mixture.
Blend well, chill dough and drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° to 375° for 3 to 4 hours until somewhat thick.
Stir and serve.

title: teatime tassies
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and butter until creamy.
Add flour; blend.
Make into 24 balls and place in pan (small muffin pan).
Flatten dough to shape of pan to form a crust.
Mix the egg, brown sugar, vanilla and butter together.
Fill dough cups with 1/3 cup chopped nuts; add mixture and top with remaining nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Great for gifts!

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Drop by spoonfuls at 350°.

title: tommie tabbs' snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together the first five items; set aside.
Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Form the dough into round spoon-size balls and roll them in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, then place them on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Serving size:
2 to 3 dozen.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Roll out; cut desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie pan, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Cook and stir beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie pan.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs with wire whisk or hand beater until almost smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes, then top with tomatoes and cheese.
Continue baking 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in 375° oven until toothpick comes out clean.

title: four gallon punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in gallon container. Fill to 1 gallon with water. Use 1 part of mixture to 3 parts water. Makes 4 gallons.

title: southern key lime pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust or use ready made.
Beat egg yolks until light yellow.
Gradually beat in lime juice.
Stir in milk and lime rind until well blended.
Add green food coloring. Pour mixture into prepared crust.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie.
Brown meringue at 325° for about 5 minutes or until light brown.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Garnish with lime slices before serving.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Cook
rice according to directions.
Brown ground meat. Add bell pepper, celery and onion and saute.
Season to taste. Lower heat,
cover
and
cook
vegetables
until tender.
Add eggplant. Cover
and cook until tender and flavors are blended.
Add
1/2 cup
water
and adjust seasoning.
Simmer a few more
minutes. Remove
from
heat.
Gradually
add hot cooked rice
until
right consistency, not too moist and not too dry. (May have
some rice left over.) Can be made ahead and reheated.

title: hamburger curry
directions: Cook noodles.
Layer in bottom of dish.
Combine cream cheese, scallions, cottage cheese and green pepper (optional).
Brown ground meat, onion, curry, garlic, salt and pepper.
Layer cheese, meat, noodles, cheese and meat.
Top with tomato sauce and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brunch eggs
directions: Layer together:
6 slices white bread, buttered and "decrusted" on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese and chopped ham.
Next, sprinkle a layer of grated Jack cheese, then diced green chilies.
Beat eggs in bowl and milk and add the following:
salt, pepper and garlic.
Mix with eggs and milk and pour over the rest.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 325° uncovered for 50 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: coconut bars
directions: Blend sugars, peanut butter and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Batter will be thick.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: crustless cheese cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes, until center is set.
If desired, shake cinnamon on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend cheeses and onion in a mixer.
Form into a ball and roll ball into nuts.
Garnish with parsley. Wrap in foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Stir cake mix and evaporated milk in bowl until just moistened.
Spread in prepared pan.
Pour pie filling evenly over top (most of the fruit will sink).
Bake 30 minutes then sprinkle with walnuts and bake 20 minutes longer until nuts are toasted.
Serves 12.
Very moist.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast.
Add all other ingredients and mix well. With a large spoon, spoon into muffin tins which have been sprayed with Pam.
Bake immediately 20-25 minutes at 400°.	Makes 2 dozen.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Mix and place a small amount on toast rounds.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan.
Broil until brown.
Serve hot.

title: sand tarts(cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well and roll into balls.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: "the best" fudge cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar into large bowl.
Combine margarine, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to rapid boil.
Pour over sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Mixture will be thin.

title: okra and rice
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add milk and corn and mix.
Spoon warm butter over top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes or until brown.

title: persimmon fudge
directions: Combine pulp, sugar, milk and syrup in large saucepan; cook slowly about 1 hour until it reaches soft ball stage.
Cool to lukewarm, stirring often.
Add butter; beat until thickens.
Then add 1 cup nuts (optional); spread into buttered dish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, margarine and 1 cup milk.
Blend well.
Take 1/2 of mixture and press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt caramels in remaining evaporated milk over medium heat.
When first of cake is done, pour melted caramels over top.
Sprinkle nuts over caramels, then sprinkle chocolate chips.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix eggs with pineapple.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon together.
Combine all ingredients.
Place in buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with ham.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli separately.
Drain broccoli and combine with rice and remaining ingredients except almonds.
Place in a greased casserole dish and top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, flour and meal and toss lightly with a fork.
Add unbeaten eggs, butter, milk and lemon rind and juice.
Beat with rotary or electric beater until smooth and thoroughly blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in moderately hot oven 35 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and orange peel.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in orange juice, eggs and vanilla (just until moistened).
