Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Fill muffin tins (greased or paper-lined) 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 1 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: mother's cream puffs
directions: Sift flour; add salt together.
Place shortening into water. Place over direct heat.
When melted, add dry ingredients all at once.
Stir constantly.
Mixture will leave bottom of pan into a smooth ball.
Remove from heat.
Cool one minute.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons 1 1/2 inches apart on greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and fill with cornstarch filling (from box of cornstarch).

title: coffee walnuts
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook to soft ball (236°).
Cool slightly.
Add 2 1/2 cups of walnuts and 1 teaspoon of vanilla. Spread in buttered pan.
Separate with a fork.
Cool.
Eat.

title: taco dip ii
directions: Mix cream cheese with dry taco seasoning.
Spread on platter. Cover with taco sauce.
Layer tomatoes, lettuce, cheese and olives.
Dip nacho chips.

title: pizza chicken
directions: You will need a baking dish lined with foil and sprayed with Pam.

title: icebox cucumbers
directions: Add salt to cucumbers; let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in covered jar.
Will keep up to 1 month in refrigerator.

title: lemon squares
directions: Cut together margarine, the 2 cups of flour, salt and 1/2 cup of sugar until particles are about the size of peas.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mint tea
directions: Bring water to a boil; add sugar, lemon juice, tea bags and mint.
Steep 15 minutes with top on.
Strain in a large pitcher. Add cold water and chill.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cut and slice onions into small pieces and saute with oil until translucent and set aside.
Cube the potatoes to 3/4-inch size and chop the celery, carrots and bell peppers into 1/2 to 1-inch sizes and set aside.
In a large cooking pot, add onions, potatoes, carrots and celery to the water and cook over low heat approximately 2 hours or until tender.
Add the bell peppers, chopped up tomatoes, string beans, various vegetables, oregano, salt and pepper.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together with mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste in large bowl.

title: quiche
directions: Fry mushrooms, onion and green pepper in garlic seasoned water.
Drain.
Mix eggs with milk and add cheese.
Stir in above ingredients and pour into shell.
Sprinkle with flour and nutmeg. Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add flour, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Add walnuts and prunes. Mix well and pour into a greased tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: tuna mix-up
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese as the box tells you to.
Cook sweet peas and carrots until tender.
Drain water off of both.
Mix macaroni and cheese up like box says and add sweet peas, carrots and tuna.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: baked rotisserie chicken
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry with paper towel. Arrange chicken in baking dish. Spray chicken with Pam, then sprinkle with rotisserie. Blend, coating well. Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: rosemary chicken
directions: Combine vinegar, mustard, garlic, onion and rosemary. Marinate chicken 3 to 12 hours before cooking.
Heat one side of grill at low to medium.
Put chicken on unlit side and bake/grill for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rocky road chocolate ice cream
directions: Soften marshmallows in 1 cup warm milk.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, then Pet milk and remaining mix and vanilla.
Stir in pudding mix, almonds and marshmallows.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: super sausage casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Put in sausage, onions and potatoes.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Bake another 20 minutes. Serves 4.

title: rye bread boat
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.
Dig out rye bread.
Cut up pieces of bread.
Put mixture in bread.
Serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the first five ingredients.
Add flour, cinnamon and nuts. Stir well but don't beat.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: white sauce for chicken
directions: Put all ingredients in a glass jar; shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: amish style mississippi mud
directions: Melt butter and brown.
Add sugar and water and boil until thick.
Mix egg yolks, flour and milk.
Add to syrup and boil until thick.
Add vanilla and put into dish.
Roll graham crackers into crumbs and spread on top.
Beat the remaining egg whites until fluffy.
Spread on top and sprinkle with a few graham cracker crumbs.
Put in oven at 350° to slightly brown top. Remove from oven and refrigerate.
Serve chilled.

title: skillet chicken with biscuit dumplings
directions: Sprinkle chicken pieces on both sides with salt and paprika. Melt butter in a large skillet. Add chicken pieces and saute until browned on both sides. Remove chicken and pour off drippings. Return chicken to skillet.
Add enough water to broth to make 1 1/2 cups.
Pour over chicken. Add minced onion, poultry seasoning and black pepper to pan. Bring to boiling. Cover and simmer 25 minutes. Add vegetables and bring to boiling again.
Top with biscuits.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer or until dumplings are cooked through. Sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon cake
directions: Bake as directed on box.
Stick holes in cake and pour over cake while still hot:
1 box powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons lemon juice.

title: can opener punch
directions: Combine juices; pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale and carbonated beverage; mix well.
Add two fifths liquor (rum or vodka).
Decorate with ice ring and fruit of your choice.

title: carrot zucchini muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Spray 12 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray or line muffin cups with paper baking cups and spray cups with nonstick cooking spray.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Simmer 3 to 4 hours, stirring often.
Add additional water if it gets too thick.
Remove bay leaf before serving over hot, cooked pasta.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: nacho bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Keep warm on the lowest setting.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crunch salad
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients until thick.
Slice apples thin.
Mix the crushed pineapple in at the time.
Toss with cool cooked mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Before serving, add peanuts.
Chill before serving.

title: layered salad
directions: Blanch vegetables in boiling water for about 1 minute.
Drain; rinse in cold water until cooled.
Mix the Hidden Valley dressing with the mayonnaise; set aside.

title: divinity
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, salt and water.
Cook to hard ball stage, stirring only until sugar dissolves.

title: pineapple-peach cobbler
directions: Melt the butter in casserole dish. Pour peaches and pineapple in dish. Mix flour, sugar and milk until smooth. Pour mixture over fruit and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Wonderful served with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat until light and lemon colored.
Add the flour and work until bowl and spoon come clean of dough.
Pinch off small piece (about size of large grape) of dough, roll into a ball and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press forefinger in center of each and fill with small amount of jelly.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°. Should be lightly brown.
If necessary, bake an extra 5 minutes or increase temperature to 375°.

title: fruity coleslaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots together.
Add salad dressing. Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add to coleslaw mixture.
Mix in marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight for best flavor.

title: quick fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Melt until smooth in saucepan over medium heat.
Add nuts and pour into buttered dish; cool.

title: roasted vegetables
directions: Chop these vegetables. You can decide on the quantity or you can use 1 cup of each.

title: texas trash
directions: Melt the first 6 ingredients and dribble over the remaining ingredients in a large roaster pan. Cook at 275° for 2 hours, stirring frequently.

title: brownie nut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour square pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until wooden pick inserted into center comes out clean.
Frost cake with 1/2 recipe fudge frosting.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cook beef, sliced onion, sliced bell pepper, soy sauce and butter until beef is done. Add gravy and simmer. Serve over rice.

title: chicken biscuit stew
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch ovenproof skillet, melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add chicken, onions, peas and carrots.
Cook until hot and bubbly.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Arrange biscuits over hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken or tenderloin stir-fry
directions: Marinate meat in sherry and soy sauce for 30 minutes.
Add meat to hot cooking oil and stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add all vegetables (except tomatoes).
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Add stock and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Stir until thick.
Add tomatoes and cook 1 minute longer.
Serve over egg noodles, rice or chow mein noodles.

title: fudgie-scotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Blend ingredients together. Press mixture into a very well greased 9-inch square pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool for 45 minutes and cut into 1 1/2 squares. Makes 36 squares.

title: creamed celery
directions: Wash and cut celery in about 1-inch lengths.
Chop onion fine. Cook celery and onions in salt water until tender.
Drain.

title: easy pineapple sauce
directions: Combine juices, pineapple, salt and sugar; mix well.
Combine 1/2 cup water and cornstarch; stir into pineapple mixture.
Bring to a boil; simmer, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter.
Serve on sliced angel food or pound cake.

title: crab spread
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a small casserole dish or pan.
Spread cocktail sauce over cream cheese (amount varies, depending on your preference).
Layer canned crab on top of cocktail sauce.
Top with sliced or chopped black olives.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beef and onions in a small amount of fat, in a heavy pan. Cook slow until meat turns white; drain.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: club cracker bars
directions: Bring margarine, sugars, graham cracker crumbs and milk to a boil and boil 5 minutes (scorches easily).
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with Club crackers.
Pour caramel sauce over.
Add another layer of Club crackers.
Pour melted frosting on top and spread.
Add finely chopped nuts on top.

title: krispie fingers or date nut balls
directions: Melt the butter; add sugar, egg, vanilla and dates.
Cook over low heat, stirring continuously until dates melt and form paste. Cool.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Form into shape of fingers and roll into coconut.

title: george washington salad
directions: Mix pineapple, Cool
Whip, pecans, Eagle Brand milk, and cherries.

title: italian goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cut cheese into strips and let melt into mixture.
Mix well.
Let simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Cook macaroni.
Drain and pour into first mixture.
Mix well. Serve with a salad and garlic bread.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream together the first 8 ingredients.
Blend in the molasses.
Add the egg.
Add alternately the flour and coffee. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets. Bake in oven preheated to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all together.
Use 3 teaspoons to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Place all ingredients into a pot; cover.
Over medium heat, cook for 50 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is no longer pink inside.
Serve over hot rice.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef with onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Drain. Layer ground beef mixture, rice, potatoes and beans in large casserole dish. Combine remaining 5 ingredients with 1/2 cup water in bowl, mixing well. Pour over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butterscotch dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, 3/4 cup water, syrup, margarine and vanilla. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Place biscuits on top.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cover and simmer 10 more minutes.
Serve warm.
Spoon sauce over and top with sour cream.

title: mama's cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo and add eggs. Mix dry ingredients together. Add dry ingredients to oleo and sugar mixture. Beat until smooth. Add vanilla. Cook in 3 cake pans at 350°.

title: spoon fudge
directions: Cook in heavy pan (iron skillet) sugar and cocoa (mix together).
Pour in cream.
Bring to boil; stir constantly until you can pick up formed ball of chocolate in water.
Take pan off stove; place pan in tap water to cool.
Add peanut butter and vanilla, stir until starts to thicken.
Pour onto greased platter. Get your spoon and eat.
Serve with popcorn.

title: pear cream cheese salad
directions: Heat 1 cup pear juice and mix with 1 package lemon jello; refrigerate until starts to jell.
Mash pears and mix with cream cheese.
Mix together with jello,
nuts and Cool Whip. Refrigerate overnight.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine and bring to rolling boil.
Boil for 2 minutes longer. Pour over 1 gallon popcorn and mix well.
Can be shaped into balls, if preferred.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Combine water, paste and French's mix and stir well.
Heat tortillas until flexible.
Dip tortillas in the sauce.
Add the ground beef and peas and sprinkle with cheese.
Roll and place on a cookie sheet.
Leave a space between each enchilada.
Pour remaining sauce over the enchiladas and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Then enchiladas freeze well.
Enjoy!

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Pour all ingredients over kraut and mix.
Put in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.

title: baked snapper almondine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Dredge fish, then saute in oil until brown on both sides.
Lay fillets in large baking dish.
Mix pepper, almonds, butter and lemon together; mix well.
Pour onto fish in baking dish.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes, or until almonds are browned.
Skin of snapper remains flat and tender when cooked.

title: breakfast before
directions: Beat eggs with milk and spices.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese, then pour liquid on top. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in zucchini, vanilla and orange peel.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Top with glaze.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in container of electric blender; process 20 seconds.
With blender on high, gradually add oil in a slow, steady stream.
Stir in poppy seed.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well in a large container. Cover and keep airtight. To prepare, combine 1/3 cup mixture in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir well.
Keep mixture refrigerated.
Yields large quantity.

title: mud cookies
directions: May add coconut if you like.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze.

title: potato and cheddar soup
directions: Bring water to boil in large saucepan; add potatoes and cook until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Measure 1 cup of reserved liquid, adding water if necessary; set aside.
Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat; add onion and cook until tender, but not brown, stirring often.
Add flour; season with pepper.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Gradually add potatoes, reserved liquid, milk and sugar to onion mixture; stir well.
Add cheese and ham.
Simmer over low heat 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: harvest casserole
directions: Mix tomatoes with hamburg and onion.
Spread on bottom of casserole dish.
Add potatoes.
Add succotash.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.
Place bread cubes on top of casserole. Pour melted butter over top.
Arrange pepper slices on top.
Bake uncovered for 1/2 hour more.

title: pineapple cake with cream cheese
directions: Use 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Oven 350°.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake for 20 minutes; cool.
Add vanilla pudding with the milk.
Add cream cheese and pineapple.
Mix well.
Spread mixture over cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip over that and sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°, rack in center of oven.
Spray nonstick cooking oil in medium to large baking dish.
Cook noodles to package directions.
Drain noodles.
Combine peas, soup and milk. Break up tuna.
Add noodles.
Mix gently and spoon into dish. Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: balsamic chicken
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. olive oil in skillet.
Add chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low.
Add garlic, oregano, salt and pepper.
Turn chicken.
Add Balsamic vinegar and remaining olive oil.
Bring to simmer.
Cover and cook over low heat until chicken is done, about 15 minutes.	Add black olives and heat until warm. Serve separately or on top of pasta.
Serves 4.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand over (evenly) crumbs.
Sprinkle with chips, then coconut, then nuts. Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes (until lightly brown). Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Prepare jello with 1 cup of hot water; set aside to cool.
Mix cottage cheese and salad dressing.
Then add cucumber and onion. Combine cottage cheese mixture with jello and refrigerate until set.
Garnish with pimento or olives.

title: beet pickles
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Cold dip and slip skins.
Slice if large beets are used.
Cover beets with mixture.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: squash fritters(hush puppies)
directions: Cook the squash in boiling water 10 to 15 minutes. Drain and mash squash to make 1 cup.
Combine squash and egg.
Stir well. Combine flour, meal, baking powder and salt. Add squash and onion. Stir. Drop into hot oil. Cook until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: cream cheese blueberry dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of the sugar and melted butter; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Soften cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add well beaten eggs, remaining sugar and vanilla; cream well.
Pour cream mixture over crumb crust; bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon blueberry fruit filling over top; refrigerate until set.
Top with whipped cream if desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Add Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip.
Save enough Cool Whip for top of pudding.
Layer in dish as you would any pudding.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well with mixer.
Cook 40 minutes in greased and floured 9x13-inch pan at 350°.

title: butterscotch apple nut cake
directions: Mix
first
9 ingredients together; add chopped apples, 1/2 cup
flour	and
butterscotch chips.
Mix well.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple beans with meatballs
directions: Mix beef, onion and salt into small balls.
Brown in oil. Drain pineapple, keeping 1/2 cup juice.
Combine juice, ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and mustard.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine meatballs, sauce, beans and pineapple in a lightly greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Add each item in order given and blend well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in batter.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) round greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: lady's damson pie
directions: *If you want meringue, reserve 3 egg whites and use 1/3 cup sugar.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light; add sugar, zucchini, oil and vanilla. Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake 60 to 65 minutes at 325° until done.

title: tortellini and cheese sauce
directions: Cook tortellini as directed.
Meanwhile, in 12-inch skillet, melt butter.
Add cream, Ricotta, Mozzarella, 2 tablespoons Parmesan and pepper.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly, until cheeses are melted and blended.
Drain tortellini; add to skillet with parsley.
Stir until well mixed.
Sprinkle with Blue cheese or Gorgonzola and additional Parmesan.
Serve immediately. Serving on heated platter will help to keep pasta from cooling too quickly.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine crushed pineapple (do not drain) with 1 cup of water. Add apricot jello and cook for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Cream the package of cream cheese; add to apricot mixture.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Prepare Dream Whip.
Beat stiff; omit vanilla.
Fold into jello mixture.
Add celery and add chopped walnuts.
Fold together and pour into large bowl.
Best made day before.

title: broccoli and chicken
directions: Cook chicken and 2 packages broccoli; drain.
Layer with broccoli, chicken and then Miracle Whip with curry powder and lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Moisten bread with 1 cup milk.
Add sugar, eggs, butter and pineapple.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strizzis linguine carciofi
directions: Over medium heat, melt the butter and add the fresh garlic. Simmer the garlic for approximately 5 minutes, being careful not to brown the garlic.
Add the heavy cream and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon glazed zucchini muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease well or paperline 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, granulated sugar, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and lemon peel.
Stir in nuts and fruit.
In small bowl, combine milk, oil and eggs until blended.
Pour into flour mixture; add zucchini, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Meanwhile, in small bowl, combine powdered sugar and lemon juice until smooth.
Drizzle over warm muffins.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions and cool.
Prepare pudding.
Crumble half of the cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Top with a layer of pudding, undrained pineapple, cherry filling, Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat all layers.
Garnish with cherries if desired.

title: cupcakes
directions: Melt butter.
Take eggs, sugar, flour, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Fill cupcake papers.
Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: jenny's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually; mix well.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Stir in sifted flour, soda, salt and oats.
Form into balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Nuts can be added.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Add seasonings to tomato juice. Freeze or can like tomato juice. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: ported jubilee crown
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving all juice and drain cherries, reserving all juice. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in reserved pineapple and cherry juices and cold water. Add pumpkin spice and salt. Blend well. Add Port.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in pineapple and cherries.
Pour into pan (I use Bundt cake pan). Chill overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: green tomato ketchup
directions: Chop or grind tomatoes. Add salt and cover with boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain. Chop or grind onions, peppers and cabbage. Add to green tomatoes and then add the sugar, vinegar and spices. Bring to a boil. Boil 10 to 15 minutes. Remove spice bag and seal in hot jars.

title: vegetarian lasagne
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan or pot.
Saute onions and garlic. Add Italian seasoning, pepper and salt.
Saute with green pepper and rest of vegetables, except spinach and mushrooms.
When onions become translucent, add rest of vegetables.
Add in tomato sauce and tomato paste with 6 ounces water.
Stir in wine, if desired. Simmer on low for 15 to 20 minutes, while adding in at last 5 to 10 minutes the mushrooms and spinach.
In large oven pan, that has been foiled or buttered, put on bottom 1/2 cup cooked sauce.
Layer with lasagne shells and Ricotta cheese.
Spread on top of shells. Build 2 layers in this fashion.
Top layer has sauce and Parmesan cheese covering very top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Allow lasagne to sit outside of oven before cutting and serving.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry out fat from sausage; do not add back in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: three bean pot
directions: Brown hamburg.
Brown bacon and onion; drain.
Mix all.
If using crock-pot, place on low for 4 to 9 hours.

title: delicious pickles
directions: Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator. Keeps 3 months in refrigerator.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put in large pot evaporated milk, rice and water.
Cook on medium heat until rice is soft and thickness you like.
About 30 minutes after it starts to boil, pour into bowl and mix in sugar and vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender.
Cool slightly. Peel potatoes and slice.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing thoroughly.
Refrigerate, covered, for several hours before serving.
Garnish with hard-cooked egg slices, parsley sprigs and/or cherry tomatoes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening 2 minutes at high speed in large bowl. Add brown
sugar to shortening and cream 3 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute at high speed after each.	Add rolled oats;
mix	a few seconds.	Sift together flour, baking powder and salt,
beating
at
high
speed, after mixing with spatula.
Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove
from sheet while hot.
Store in jar or tins; will remain crispy for days.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Flatten biscuits with hand.
Wrap each biscuits around an apple half.
Place side down in 2 greased 9 x 11 inch baking dishes.
Combine sugar, water, butter and vanilla.
Pour 1 2/3 cups into each pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon over dumplings.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown, and apples are tender.
Serve warm.

title: golden chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In
quart
pan
heat water to boiling.
Add potatoes and onion.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add
frozen
vegetables.
Cover;
simmer
5 more minutes.
Drain.
Add	in
pan
chicken gravy and poultry seasoning.	Spoon into 9-inch
pie pans.
Unroll rolls without separating pieces.	Firmly press down to seal.
Cut dough into 8 lengthwise strips about 3/4-inch wide.
Arrange dough strips over chicken
mixture to form lattice.
Fold long ends under. Bake 30 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain, reserving 1/2 cup of liquid.
Saute onions in butter.
Add all ingredients together, except Ritz crackers.
Put into greased dish.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top of casserole; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into serving size pieces. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place on rack in shallow baking pan. Roast in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Turn and brown other side. Drain fat and put ribs in slow cooker. Combine bouillon with brown sugar and soy sauce. Pour over ribs. Cover and cook on low for 6 to 8 hours. Turn control to high. Add onion and dissolve cornstarch in small amount of cold water. Stir into pot. Cover and cook on high another 10 to 15 minutes or until slightly thickened. Stir in oranges and green pepper; cover and cook 5 minutes. Serve over cooked rice or crisp Chinese noodles.

title: easy butter cookies
directions: In large bowl, add sugar and melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Slowly add mixture of flour and baking powder.
Knead with hands.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Best if used with cookie press.
Decorate and bake!

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: cabbage beef casserole
directions: Place chopped cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown meat and onions.
Add meat, onions and rice to chopped cabbage.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add more water, if needed.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain liquid from asparagus into a saucepan; add 1/2 stick butter.
Heat.
Make a paste of milk and cornstarch.
Add to hot liquid.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Make several slits in lamb.
Place a piece of garlic in each slit.
Rub lamb with thyme, rosemary, salt and pepper.
Place lamb on rack in roasting pan in 325° oven.
Roast for 1 1/2 hours for medium rare and 2 1/2 hours for medium.

title: layered chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Put 1 package cookie mix, cut into slices, into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add sugar, vanilla and nuts to softened cream cheese, beat until creamy.
Spread on top of cookie layer.
Top with cookie slices from second roll of cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until creamy.
Add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour and salt, at low speed.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1-1/2 hours.

title: easy buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add lard and salt.
Add flour to make stiff (not sticky or not too stiff).
Knead until smooth. Let rise until dough is double in size.
Shape into buns (about 30).
Let rise again.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375° until browned.

title: kate's pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla. Mix well. Add slightly beaten eggs. Add chopped pecans and stir well. Pour in pie crust and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: hot tamales or sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; add onions, celery and green peppers.
Drain fat. Add vinegar, tomato soup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: regal curried chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour; brown in butter in a large skillet. Remove chicken to a 2-quart casserole, reserving pan drippings in skillet.
Set chicken aside.
Saute onion and garlic in pan drippings until onion is tender.
Stir in curry powder, ginger and salt, blending well.
Add next 4 ingredients and stir well.
Pour over chicken in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve over rice.
Serve curry with several of the following condiments: flaked coconut, toasted almonds, chopped peanuts, pineapple chunks, chutney, diced tomato, chopped banana and chopped hard cooked egg.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Fry bacon in Dutch oven until crisp.
Remove bacon but retain 1/2 of the bacon grease.
Saute onion, pepper, celery and garlic until tender.
Add water and bring to boil.
Add beans, carrots, bacon, salt, pepper, basil, dill weed and oregano.
Return to boil.
Cover and cook; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add potatoes and return to boil.
Cover; simmer additional 10 to 15 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Drain.

title: nana's bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour boiling water over All-Bran.
Let it stand.
Cream sugar and eggs.
Beat well for 50 strokes.
Mix in oil.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: mary lunceford's corn pudding
directions: Blend corn and sugar in a bowl.
Beat eggs slightly and add to corn.
Blend the flour, 2 or 3 tablespoons, at a time.
Dot with butter.

title: turkey tot casserole
directions: Brown ground turkey in pan.
Drain and spread in 8 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix in green beans and cream of mushroom soup, then salt and pepper.
Layer top with Tater Tots.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cheese and let melt approximately 5 minutes.
Serve.

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, pumpkin pie spice, baking soda and salt.
In small mixer bowl, beat eggs.
Beat in sugar, oil and pumpkin.

title: cheese delight
directions: Combine gelatin and water.
Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in cheese, drained pineapple and whipped cream.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: You will also need rolling pin, cookie cutters, cookie sheet, toothpick, waxed paper, acrylic paint, artist's brush, plastic straw and ribbon.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add flour, butter, sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Whip Dream Whip and fold into cooled egg mixture.
Drain pineapple chunks and oranges.
Fold in all fruit, marshmallows and nutmeats.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut crispy chicken
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken breasts into this mixture and then into stuffing mix.
Roll into peanuts. Place in shallow baking pan.
Pour butter over chicken breasts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: beef and macaroni dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed on box.
Fold in beef, tomatoes and milk.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Can be reheated on stove.

title: roast beef with wine and vegetables
directions: Make a few slits with a sharp knife in the roast.
Insert 1 garlic clove and parsley sprig in each hole.
Pour wine and olive oil over meat.
Sprinkle generously with salt, pepper and oregano. It is safest to use a meat thermometer to obtain the desired degree of doneness.
Bake at 350° for three hours or until done.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter and 1 cup sugar; mix well. Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Stir into potato mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add 6 tablespoons sugar slowly, beating constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until stiff. Spread meringue over top of pie, sealing to edge.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Chill pie before serving.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flavoring, butter, cinnamon and egg.
Add milk slowly and stir constantly.
Add bread and raisins.
Mix and pour into well buttered baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: coconut icing
directions: Beat all ingredients until fluffy and smooth.

title: grandma's one bowl applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Cut in butter.
Add beaten egg, molasses and applesauce.
Beat well by hand.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Turn out on cake rack and sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
You may glaze with 3 tablespoons of lemon juice and enough powdered sugar to make a thick glaze.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: icing - japanese cake
directions: Combine all and boil until thick.
Remove from heat.
Drain juice from small can of pineapple and add the pineapple to cooked mixture.
Spread between cake layers, top and sides.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Place beef cubes in bowl.
Add salt, pepper and oregano to olive oil.
Sprinkle over beef.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Skewer beef cubes, olives and vegetables alternating using 1/4 of each on each skewer.
Place skewers on broiler rack.
Broil until beef is brown, turning to brown evenly.
Remove from skewers onto serving plate.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana icing
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed, beating well after each addition. Beat at high speed of mixer until creamy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: lela engling's chicken almond casserole
directions: Saute celery, onions and mushrooms in butter.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Combine noodles and sauteed vegetables with remaining ingredients (except almonds) and pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: date roll
directions: Cook white and brown sugars and milk together to soft ball stage, then add chopped dates.
Cook to firm, but not hard, ball stage.
Then remove from heat.
Add nuts, butter and vanilla. Beat until stiff consistency to roll in wet cloth into log.
Slice and store in sealed container.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a bowl and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar.
Then add eggs one at a time.
Then mix in the vanilla, orange peel, zucchini, milk and walnuts.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix oleo, pecans and flour together.
Press into oblong pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix powdered sugar, vanilla and cream cheese together until creamy. Add Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture over cooled crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: chocolate fudge icing
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk. Stir and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly, for one minute.
Remove from heat, cool and beat until thick enough to spread a thin layer on cake or brownies.
(Nuts optional.)

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Spread refried beans on bottom of pan, then spread sour cream over all.
Place shredded cheeses over that.
Top with onion, pepper, mushrooms and olives.
Add tomato.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: elbow macaroni salad
directions: Cook elbow macaroni.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Garnish with radish roses, if desired.
Serve on lettuce.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Place all ingredients in a large container with lid.
Shake well.
Mix 2 tablespoons of mixture with 8 ounces of very hot water for individual servings.
Adjust amount of mixture for individual taste.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: cream of chicken with poppy seed casserole
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Layer chicken in casserole dish. Pour sour cream mixture over chicken.
Mix cracker crumbs with butter and place on top.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly around edges.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough ketchup for moisture to mixture (to taste).
Put mixture in 3-quart dish.
Drizzle more ketchup on top of mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and punch 1 hole in center.
Microwave on High for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together twice.
Put juice of one orange in cup. Add 2 tablespoons melted shortening and fill remainder of cup to 3/4 full with boiling water.
Add with 1 egg to dry ingredients and mix together.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts and 1 cup raw cranberries.
Pour into lightly greased pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 small loaf cakes.
Delicious served warm with butter.

title: cheese logs
directions: Mix and roll in logs.
It makes 2 about 1/2-inch around. Sprinkle with cracked black pepper, the more pepper the hotter. Serve with Town House crackers.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Mix together, spread half in a large cake pan and chill until firm.
Take out, spread with 1 pint of sour cream and pour rest of jello mixture on top.
Chill until set.
Decorate and cut into serving pieces.
Takes 3 hours to make.

title: stir-fry beef, pork or chicken
directions: Cut meat into small strips.
In bowl, toss meat with the soy sauce, oil, sugar, cornstarch and hot pepper sauce.
Cut celery, carrot and green pepper into matchstick thin strips.
In a 12-inch skillet over high heat in very hot oil, cook vegetables, stirring frequently until tender-crisp.
Remove vegetables to a bowl.
In drippings in skillet, cook the meat, stirring quickly and constantly.
Return vegetables and mix well.
Serve over rice.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water until they come to a boil.
Turn stove down and add bacon bits, carrots, chicken soup and celery soup. Mix thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add evaporated milk and simmer until done.
Stir often to keep from sticking or scorching.
Can add parsley flakes, if desired.

title: cherry pies
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar, then add Cool Whip and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well, then pour into graham cracker crust pie shells.
Top with cherry pie filling and chill.

title: venison summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into rolls.
Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Take off foil and bake on racks a little over an hour, turning once, at 300°.
Will keep for 3 weeks in refrigerator or can be frozen.

title: baked northern pike
directions: Place slices of pike in greased baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place slices of onion on fish.
Spoon tomatoes over onion.
Crumble basil over tomatoes.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour or until fish flakes easily.
Good served with baked potatoes, carrot casserole and celery, apricot pie for dessert.

title: zucchini sticks
directions: Slice zucchini into stick forms.
Sprinkle with garlic, olive oil and soy sauce.
Marinate 30 minutes.
Roll zucchini sticks in flour.
Dip in beaten eggs, then coat with bread crumbs.
Deep-fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: bonnie's fudge pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, combine shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Blend until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and baking soda. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine
the first 8 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; let it boil
for
minutes.
Set
it
aside;
let it cool for 45 minutes.
Combine the last 3 ingredients (being careful to get lumps
out	of baking soda).
Make a hole in the center of dry mixture;
pour liquid mixture into it.
Mix well.
Pour into a well
buttered
10-inch
spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool
for
minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle nuts in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: avocado bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add mashed
avocado and beaten eggs. Mix dry ingredients and sift.
Add	to creamed mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until done.

title: sour cream spanish rice
directions: Mix sour cream, green chilies and 1 cup of the olives, sliced. Place a layer of the rice in a buttered 2-quart casserole, then a layer of sour cream mixture and a layer of cheese strips from the Monterey Jack.
Repeat.
Top layer must be rice.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cover top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika and dot with whole pitted ripe olives.
Bake another 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 8.

title: pear tart
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Add ice water.
Toss and push together in a ball and flour sides.
Refrigerate about 10 to 15 minutes.
Take out of refrigerator and roll out into pie pan. Prick with a fork.
Bake until light brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup and horseradish.
Blend ketchup and horseradish to taste; set aside.

title: chili beans
directions: Use enough water to cover beans.
Check frequently.
Add water, if needed.
Cook on low heat.
Do not boil.
Add tomato sauce, when beans are tender (approximately 2 hours).

title: crumbly-goodie dessert
directions: Mix together well the first 4 ingredients and spread out on cookie sheet.
Cook 15 or 20 minutes at 375°.
Let cool, then crumble.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Add the soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Add the broccoli.
Mix together and put in 3-quart casserole.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon acorn squash
directions: Halve and core squash; place halves in baking dish, cut side down.
Fill pan with about 1/2-inch water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Turn squash over and fill cavity with pat of butter.
Sprinkle surface of cavity with 1 tablespoon of sugar or to desired sweetness.
Generously dust with cinnamon and bake for 15 minutes more.
Serve individually in small bowls. Even little children like this because it tastes like cinnamon toast.
Serves 4.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream all ingredients until blended.
Chill in container. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: dabo colo
directions: Mix and let chill.
Roll out in very thin rolls (smaller than pencil).
Cut into tiny pieces with scissors.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until lightly roasted.
Enjoy this snack!

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat in a Dutch
oven.
Drain
fat.
Add	a small amount of margarine to
lightly saute celery, onions and green pepper. Add all other
ingredients,
except
barley and rice. Cook until carrots are
tender,
about
40 minutes, uncovered. Add barley and rice.
Stir
occasionally,
cooking
about
30 minutes more. Makes 6 to 8 generous servings.

title: pecan bite-size tarts(makes 24)
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat softened butter and cream cheese until thoroughly combined. Stir in the flour. Using 24 ungreased 1 3/4 inch muffin cups, press a round tsp of pastry evenly into the bottom and up the sides of each cup.

title: baked corn with sour cream
directions: Cook onion in butter; blend in flour and salt.
Add sour cream gradually, stirring to keep smooth.
Bring just to a boil and add corn.
Cook until heated through.
Pour in greased baking dish. Garnish with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Marinate chicken in last five ingredients several hours, then grill.
Place chicken on tortillas.
Serve with fresh avocado, grated cheese, green and red peppers, onions, tomatoes and sour cream.
Serves 4.

title: reese cup blossoms
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and place in ungreased miniature tins.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Press in Reese's cups.
Cool 10 minutes in freezer.
Use butter knife to remove from tins.

title: round steak and gravy
directions: Sprinkle meat with flour; cut into serving pieces.
Melt shortening; brown meat.
Put onion soup mix over meat.
Mix water and soup; pour over.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Sift soda and salt with flour.
Mix firm butter and flour together until it looks like crumbs.
Add brown sugar, then nuts. Beat eggs together until light; mix into the dough which will be rather firm.
Knead until smooth, then make into the size roll desired.
Wrap in waxed paper; place in refrigerator overnight or until thoroughly chilled.
Slice cookies very thin; place on greased baking sheet and bake at 350° until light brown, approximately 12 minutes.
This dough will keep for several days. Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.
Keep in tightly covered container.

title: roasted potato salad
directions: *I use 1/2 bottle Hormel real bacon pieces (2 ounces).

title: hot crab dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt the butter. Add flour.
Mix well. Gradually add milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted. Blend in green onion, Worcestershire sauce, parsley and crabmeat.
Heat just until bubbly. Serve warm.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: pea salad
directions: Toss ingredients with desired amount of mayonnaise.
Chill.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Sauce:
Pour 3 cups evaporated milk in saucepan.
Supplement last 1 1/4 cups with water.
Add 5 heaping tablespoons flour and stir out all lumps.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place 1 stick margarine in saucepan and stir over medium-low flame until thickened.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onions, salt, eggs and milk.
Form into meat balls and brown in oleo or butter or shortening.
Drain and arrange in casserole dish.
Add soup (prepared as on can).
Top with Tater Tots and bake until golden brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Pour water over apples.
(Blend together sugar, flour and oleo until crumbly.)
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes(heart smart)
directions: With a sharp knife, slice tops of tomatoes.
With a grapefruit spoon, remove pulp.
Drain upside down on paper towels.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spoon on equal amount into tomatoes.
Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: aunt joyce's chewy cake squares
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into lightly greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and corn muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients, add milk slowly and mix well.
Add other ingredients and turn into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: aunt nancy's cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion together.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix caramels and milk together over low heat until melted.
Pour on top of cooked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over caramel mixture.
Add the remainder of the batter and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool completely before cutting.

title: sauteed venison tenderloin
directions: Slice venison tenderloin into 1/2 inch medallions.
Pound gently on both sides and rinse.
Put flour in a Ziploc bag. Place meat in bag; shake vigorously.
Meanwhile, melt butter. Saute onion and garlic in butter until tender, not brown.
Remove meat from flour, shaking off excess flour.
Place in hot butter; let cook until brown on both sides.
Stir meat to blend butter and flour.
Add apple cider.
Stir to blend the roux and cider.
Lower heat and let thicken.
Add salt, pepper and applesauce.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Cook turkey meat in a bowl in the microwave about 5 minutes. Cover with wax paper, check and stir.
Drain well.
Combine next 3 ingredients and saute over medium heat in chicken broth.
Add cooked turkey after vegetables are cooked.
Add next 3 ingredients and stir well.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients.
Deep fry wings; drain on paper towels.
Dip wings in hot sauce and bake 10 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix together, adding garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce. Cook in double boiler or microwave until cheese melts.

title: fresh cucumber slices
directions: Layer sliced cucumber slices and onion in a large bowl. Combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour marinade over cucumbers.
Cover and chill cucumbers for at least 2 hours. Use slotted spoon to serve chilled cucumber slices.

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Layer ingredients (in order listed) in greased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: flaky italian biscuits
directions: Combine biscuit mix and spice in a bowl. Stir in milk just until moistened. Place on a floured board; knead 10 to 15 times. Roll out to 1/2-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:	8 biscuits.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes slowly until soft, yet firm.
In bowl combine other ingredients and whip until smooth.
Cook over low heat until becomes thickened.
Combine diced potato mixture, parsley, onion, celery and celery seed.

title: middletown oyster stew
directions: In frying pan, put oil and diced salt pork; fry slowly, turning constantly until crisp and brown.
Put into a 3-quart cooking pot.
Add oysters (there is some juice in the oysters), stirring constantly and gradually add water or juice. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a slow boil and cook about 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Pour in casserole dish. Cover with chips or potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix by hand and freeze in 5 quart freezer.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, substitute seasoned salt for regular salt, if desired.
Drain well.
Cool to room temperature.
Spoon into a large bowl.
Add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently with a fork.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, add cashews, if desired.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Mix well the brown sugar, ketchup and water in a small bowl. Lay chops in pan; salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over chops.
Place 1 onion slice over each chop.
Cover with foil; bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove foil and finish baking 1/2 hour more.

title: pumpkin ice cream squares
directions: Early in day or day ahead, in large bowl mix first 7 ingredients.
Fold in softened ice cream until well blended. Arrange half of gingersnap cookies in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Spoon half mixture over cookies.
Top with remaining cookies, then ice cream mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze for 5 hours.
In small bowl, whip cream until stiff peaks form.
Score top of ice cream into 15 servings.
Top each piece with cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Return to freezer until ready to serve.

title: pie crusts
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add water and mix thoroughly. Roll on floured board to desired thickness.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves and let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix meat, rice, salt, pepper, onion and egg. Roll a portion of meat mixture into each cabbage leaf.
Fasten leaf with a toothpick.
Place cabbage rolls into baking dish. Pour soup and water over and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
May also be cooked in pressure cooker; place rolls in cooker on rack. Pour soup and water over rolls.
Set control at 15 and cook 8 minutes.
After control reaches pressure, reduce pressure normally for 5 minutes, then run pan under cold water.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt cheese, butter and pour milk into a double boiler.
Put a layer of broccoli and a layer of cracker crumbs until all is used.
Then pour the cheese sauce over it.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°

title: crock-pot bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat on low in crock-pot overnight or all day!
Delicious!

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet; drain off fat and measure. Return 1/4 cup of fat to skillet.
Add celery and onion.
Cook 1 minute.
Blend in flour.
Slowly stir in water and vinegar; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in sugar, salt and pepper.

title: cornbread
directions: Scald half and half and butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix in eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry onions, green peppers and mushrooms in oil.
Add hamburg. Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, sauce and paste together in a large kettle.
Mix well.
Season with 4 shakes of Italian seasoning, 3 shakes oregano and salt and pepper to taste.
Add crushed garlic. Cook uncovered, simmering 4 to 6 hours or longer.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: raspberry carousel(salad)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry juice and chill until slightly thick.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts. Pour in dish or mold.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Heat 1 cup water and 1 stick margarine to boiling.
Add 1 cup flour and stir.
Let cool.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, stirring with a fork.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix pudding and milk until thick.
Then add cream cheese.
Pour mixture over crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix baking mix, Sprite and sour cream.
Roll out onto floured pastry sheet to 1 inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutters and place on cookie sheet.
Melt 1/4 cup butter. Brush over biscuits. Bake at 375° until brown.

title: play dough
directions: In saucepan, mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
Cook 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from side of pan.
Knead slightly.
Store in airtight containers.
Keeps 3 months.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoon in hot oil. Drain on paper towel.
Cook until brown.

title: strawberry torte
directions: Crush wafers with rolling pin.
Put a layer of wafers at the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Save enough for top.
Cream the butter and powdered sugar well. Add egg yolks, one at a time; beat well.
Fold in beaten stiff egg whites.
Place on top of crust. Place nuts on top of this mixture, then strawberries on top. Place whipped cream, beaten stiff, as next layer, then remaining wafer crumbs on top.
Chill in refrigerator 1 hour before serving.

title: amy's peanut butter granola
directions: Measure the oats, wheat germ, sesame seed and coconut into the baking pan.
Stir with rubber scraper to mix.
In a small bowl, use the rubber scraper to stir together the peanut butter, honey, cooking oil, vanilla and salt.
Pour over the oat mixture.
Stir with rubber scraper until all is coated.
Put pan into oven.
Turn oven to 300°.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir mixture with a pancake turner to break up.
Let granola cool. Makes about 6 cups.
Store in covered container.

title: mama sue's orange cake
directions: Grind orange and raisins (rind and all on orange) together. Save 1/3 cup of this for icing. Cream Crisco and sugar. Add egg and mix well. Add vanilla. Add flour and soda alternately with sour milk. Add orange and raisin mix. Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter tarts
directions: Spoon a tablespoon of whipped topping into the bottom of each tart shell. Set aside. In a mixing bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until well mixed. Add pudding mix. Beat 1 minute. Fold in remaining whipped topping. Spoon about 1/2 cup filling into each shell. Chill.

title: strawberry pizza dessert
directions: Bake sugar dough and cool as directed on pizza pan.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until spreadable (may use some milk, if needed) and spread on cookie dough.
Top with strawberry glaze and fresh strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli and rice.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: aloha beef kabobs
directions: Slice steak into 1/4-inch thick strips and place in shallow nonaluminum pan or dish. Combine seasonings.
Mix soy sauce, lemon juice and oil.
Add this mixture to the seasonings and mix well. Pour marinade over steak strips and allow meat to marinate in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Thread marinated meat on skewers, accordian style, alternating tomatoes, pepper or mushrooms between steak.
Brush with marinade and grill or place in broiler 4-inches from heat.
Grill 3 minutes. Turn, marinade and grill other side.

title: 3-flavored bread
directions: Combine 2 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast in mixing bowl; mix well.
Add margarine and very warm water to the flour yeast mix.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed about 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1 more cup of flour. Beat at high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Divide dough in 3 equal parts.
To 1/3 of dough, add 2 tablespoons molasses and wheat flour.
If necessary, add a little more flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny, about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning over once to grease top.
Cover and set aside.
To the second 1/3 dough, add caraway seed, cocoa, 2 tablespoons molasses and rye bread flour.
If necessary, add more flour to make a soft dough. Knead about 5 minutes on a floured surface until smooth and satiny. Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top; set aside.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in a bag.
Add chops, a few at a time, and shake to coat.
Brown chops in small amount of oil. Quarter apricots; add with onions to pot.
Pour juice from apricots over meat.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Allow juices to thicken.

title: dill pickles
directions: Boil all ingredients.
Cut and rinse cucumbers.
Put in jars and put a piece of fresh dill or dill seed and 1/4 teaspoon alum in each jar.
Cover with mix to top; set aside with lids on for 6 days, then put in dark place for 8 weeks.

title: monterey jack cheese bread
directions: Cut the loaf of French bread in half lengthwise.
Then generously spread the Parkay on both pieces of French bread. Next, put a layer of Miracle Whip.
Finish with the shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Don't let cheese get brown, but you want the bread to get crisp.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients and pour into a buttered Pyrex dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and sprinkle on top of casserole.
Melt 1 stick of margarine and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: texas three alarm chili
directions: Brown meat; add tomato sauce and 2 cans of water.
Add all dry ingredients except the mesa flour.
Simmer covered for 1 hour.
Mix mesa flour with warm water to form a thick but flowable paste.
Add to mixture and cook for 20 more minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and peanut butter together; add eggs. Beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to first mixture.
Form into balls.
Flatten with fork.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli swiss cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, covered in a small amount boiling water 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, butter and flour in container of an electric blender; process until smooth.
Set aside.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix with mayonnaise and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: new orleans bean soup
directions: Peel and chop onion; rinse celery and carrot.
Cut into thin strips.
Cut ham into cubes or strips.
In a large saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add celery, carrot and garlic.
Saute for a few minutes until soft but not brown.
Add kidney beans with liquid, ham and water; bring to a boil.
Add crumbled bouillon cube.
Cook soup for a couple of minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce, parsley, thyme, bay leaves and lemon juice. Bring to a boil again.
Cook for about 15 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve piping hot.
You may season the soup with 1/2 tablespoon of molasses or 1 tablespoon of brown sugar.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately; mix well.
Add flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: miss prissy and miss scarlett's vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until sugar dissolves; add enough milk to fill line on 1 gallon tank.
Freeze.
Best recipe in the South.

title: carrot bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
In a bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs; blend well all dry ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Stir in carrots and nuts. Pour into loaf pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: oven-browned rice
directions: Melt margarine in skillet, saute onion until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
together and let stand overnight. In the morning, drain and squeeze out the liquid.
Add celery, vinegar and sugar.
Boil 25 minutes.
Take off heat and drain off all vinegar.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix and can.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: frito pie
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add chili mix and sauce; simmer for 10 minutes.
Use deep baking dish.
Layer, starting with Fritos, beans, onions, chili and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, placing whites in a large bowl, yolks in another large bowl.
Let egg whites warm to room temperature (about 1 hour).

title: biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break bread into small chunks.
Place in a large bowl.
Add milk and let soak 10 minutes.
Work mixture with hands until milk is absorbed.
Combine eggs and next four ingredients.
Stir into bread mixture.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: ham, chicken or turkey tetrazzini(serves 8)
directions: In medium pan, melt butter and stir in flour; add chicken broth and milk and heat until thick.
Stir in rest of ingredients. Remove from heat and stir in mayonnaise.
Oil 9 x 13-inch baking dish; layer asparagus, ham and spaghetti.
Pour sauce over top and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: greek spaghetti quickie
directions: Prepare spaghetti.
Add Greek dressing, salt, pepper and spices.
Add tomatoes, olives and cheese.
May be served hot or cold.
Great served with kabobs and pita bread.

title: broccoli with red peppers
directions: Cut off broccoli flowerets and slice the stems to make diagonal pieces.
Saute the broccoli and pepper pieces in the oil with the garlic over medium-high heat for 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn the heat to medium and add the chicken broth a little at a time, stirring frequently.
Continue to add the broth, cooking and stirring until the broccoli is done as desired, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Garnish with the lemon zest and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in margarine.
Mix in nuts.
Drop by spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: jonathan's berries "n" bits
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and water.
Beat in pudding, mix well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 2 cups into a 3-quart glass bowl.
Top with 1/2 of each pie mix, wafers, strawberries and chocolate bits.
Repeat layering.
Garnish with additional bits, wafers and strawberries.
Chill thoroughly. Serve with additional whipped cream.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: raw potato pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks; stir in grated potatoes and a mixture of the flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Beat the egg whites until rounded peaks are formed.
Fold into the potato mixture. Spoon about 2 tablespoons of batter for each pancake into hot fat in skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Serve with applesauce or molasses, if you like.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Press in pie plate and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: jigglers(creamy style)
directions: Pour gelatin in 2 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Cool in room temperature for 30 minutes.
Pour 1 cup cold milk into a shaker; add pudding and shake.
Open shaker; pour pudding quickly into gelatin.
Stir with a wire whisk into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Cut into squares or use cookie cutters for a special design.

title: chicken chili stew
directions: Saute onion, garlic and pepper in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese, sour cream or green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 6.

title: oven-made caramel corn
directions: Spread freshly popped corn in a large, shallow sheet pan.
Put corn in a low heat oven (250°) to keep warm and crisp.
Combine butter, brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in a 2 quart heavy saucepan.
Place on medium heat; stir until sugar dissolves. Continue to boil to the firm ball stage (248° thermometer), about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir well. Add to corn, mixing well.
Return to oven (250°) for 45 to 50 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 425° until brown.

title: pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle on medium-high heat and lightly grease.
Put egg in bowl and beat with a fork.
Add milk and oil; mix with fork.
Add dry ingredients, except berries, and mix with fork. Add berries, if desired.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients into bowl.
Add melted butter and milk.
Pour into greased baking pan (8 x 6 x 2-inch).
Mix cherries or peaches with sugar; pour over batter.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt the butter in a 9 x 13 pan. Mix together flour, milk and sugar. Pour over melted butter and then add peaches over the mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and egg; set aside.
Mix water and yeast.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add flour.
Melt butter in bowl.
Pull off pieces of dough, about the size of a biscuit, and dip in butter. Place in Bundt pan.
Pour remaining butter over bread.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours in a warm place.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: baked shrimp with stuffed mushrooms
directions: Peel and clean shrimp; season.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Add sherry and lemon juice.
Add seasoned shrimp to baking dish and bake at 375 degrees 10-15 minutes.
Baste with butter mixture occasionally.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In 4-quart microproof bowl mix sugar, milk and butter.
Cook on High (maximum power) 20 to 22 minutes or until a few drops of mixture in cold water forms a soft ball.
Stir well every 5 minutes while cooking.
Stir in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream until mixture is well blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square dish for thick pieces or 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish for thinner pieces.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cookies
directions: Sift flour in a large mixing bowl.
Make hole in center.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well with hand until makes stiff dough. Roll out on floured board real thin.
Cut out.
Bake on cookie sheet until done.
Top with Chocolate Icing or Egg White Icing.

title: bach home's corn bread salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Crumble muffins; mix with vegetables and mayonnaise.
Stir in tomatoes and seasonings. Sprinkle with bacon.

title: pecan pie(best of show - 1993 jones county fair)
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Blend in beaten eggs, vanilla, pecans (chopped), syrup, salt and sugar.
Add ingredients to pie shell.
Carefully place pecan halves in design of choice on top of filling.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until edges are golden brown.
Cool to room temperature.

title: crumb cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time and beat well after each egg.
Fold in coconut, graham cracker crumbs and vanilla.
Add nuts last.
Pour in 2 (9-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cheng du chicken(serves 4)
directions: Mix sherry, 2 tablespoons soy sauce, pepper and cornstarch. Add chicken and refrigerate 15 minutes or longer to marinate.
In wok or skillet, heat cooking oil.
Saute green pepper, garlic, ginger, onion, snow peas and broccoli.
Then add the chicken mixture until chicken is white through.
Add red pepper flakes, vinegar, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, sesame seed oil and peanuts. Cook 3 minutes and serve over rice.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, water and rice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a large baking dish.
Layer chicken pieces on top of mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast beef and potatoes
directions: Wash roast and cook in slow cooker (crock pot) overnight or all day.
Remove and place in covered casserole dish.
Put potatoes and carrots around meat.
Cut up onions, bell pepper and celery and scatter around potatoes and carrots.
Season with meat tenderizer, onion salt and lots of Worcestershire sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325 degrees for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Cream sugar with margarine.
Add egg, vanilla and flour. Last, add coconut.
Beat on low with mixer, then beat by hand. Save 1 cup batter to crumble on top.
Spread batter on 11 x 17-inch cookie sheet, then pour pineapple filling over entire batter; crumble remaining batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: In a fry pan crumble beef and sausage; fry until brown.
In a big saucepan put first 11 ingredients as in spaghetti sauce.

Cook noodles in a separate pan approximately 18 minutes; then drain. Place 1/2 cup of the noodles in bottom of a large baking dish; add and spread 1/3 of meat mixture, 1/2 of Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layer again (noodles, meat mixture and cheeses).
Put remaining sauce on top and sprinkle with Romano cheese.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix broth, soup and chicken in pot.
Bring to boil; pour into baking dish.
Mix flour, milk, baking powder, salt and pepper; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine milk, broth and flour in large saucepan and heat.
Add cheese and simmer until cheeses melt completely and soup has thick consistency.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Sift flour with salt and add to shortening mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Shape into crescents.
Bake in pan at 325° about 20 minutes.
Do not brown.

title: baklava(delicious greek dessert)
directions: Grind nuts coarsely.
Mix with sugar, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg.
Line two baking pans, 10 x 15 x 2-inch with a sheet of filo and brush each generously with butter.
Continue this process until you have 6 filo in each pan, each generously buttered. Sprinkle the top filo with a layer of nut mixture.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together salt, Crisco, and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Sift flour; add gradually to mixture; add vanilla. Beat well and bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: salt ceramic
directions: Mix together in a double boiler placed over heat.
Stir constantly and in about 2 or 3 minutes it becomes thick.
It quickly reaches a consistency similar to bread dough and is then placed on a piece of wax paper or aluminum foil and allowed to cool.

title: busy-day pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Put meat in a heavy Dutch oven.
Mix remaining ingredients in a small bowl; spread over top and sides of roast.
Cover and bake for about 3 hours, until tender.
Lift meat to cutting board.
Let stand about 5 minutes, then cut into thin slices.
Pour gravy into a sauceboat to spoon over each serving.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix jello, sugar and pineapple (with juice) in saucepan.
Cook until red.
Cool.
Fold into cottage cheese, nuts and Cool Whip. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish. Chill.

title: frosted strawberry squares
directions: Thaw strawberries; set aside.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (40 minutes if you double recipe).
Stir occasionally while baking.
Spread 2/3 of crumbs in 9 x 9-inch container; let cool.
Beat 2 egg whites, add 1 cup sugar and beat until very stiff.
Fold in 2 cups strawberries, more nuts and add 2 cups whipped topping.
Pour over crumbs and sprinkle crumbs on top.
Freeze.
Remove from freezer for 15 to 20 minutes before eating.

title: layered banana pineapple dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, Sweet 'N Low and margarine well in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press evenly onto bottom of pan.
Arrange banana slices on crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gradually beat in milk.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat until well blended.
Spread evenly over banana slices.
Spoon pineapple evenly over pudding mixture. Spread whipped topping over pineapple.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until ready to serve.
This is a dessert that most diabetics can eat.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat well until creamy.
Sift together next 4 ingredients.
Mix with creamed mixture.
Add nuts. Fold in apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's cobbler
directions: Pour fruit into greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top. Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: carrots in orange juice
directions: Grate on fine grater one pound of carrots.
Sprinkle with 2 to 4 teaspoons of sugar.
Add orange juice as needed to moisten. Some carrots need more orange juice than others and more or less sugar added to taste.

title: fruit cup
directions: Mix together any two or more of the fruits.
Serve cold.
Some fruits turn brown after being cut.
To prevent this, dip them in a small amount of lemon juice or orange juice right after cutting.

title: puffs
directions: Bring margarine and oleo to a boil; add flour.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each. Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.
Split in half and fill with chicken salad, tuna or ham salad.

title: coconut balls
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, dates and vanilla.
Beat egg; add mixture to egg.
Mix Rice Krispies and pecans.
