Pour hot mixture over Rice Krispies and pecans.
Roll into small balls and in coconut.

title: texas cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly and add milk.
Mix flour, cornstarch and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add to first mixture with butter.
Cook over low flame or in double boiler until thickened.

title: amuma delfina's chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour. Bring margarine, water and cocoa to boil. Pour over flour and sugar and mix well. Add eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon, soda and vanilla. Pour into greased jellyroll pan (13 x 8-inches). Bake 25 minutes at 375°. While cake is baking, prepare the icing.

title: creamed tuna on toast
directions: Mix butter, flour,
pepper
and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add tuna, stir and spoon onto toast.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash and drain sauerkraut.
Drain bean sprouts.
Heat sugar and vinegar, then cool.
Pour over sauerkraut, sprouts, onion and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain and serve.

title: honey glazed ham
directions: Score ham.
Place ham, fat side up, on rack in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Baste ham with mixture during last 1/2 hour of cooking.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add sugar and stir to mix thoroughly.
Make a well in the center of dry ingredients and add, all at once, oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix well; add nuts.
Pour batter into four 8 x 4-inch loaf pans, filling each half-full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of the loaf comes out clean.
Yield:
4 loaves (16 slices each).
Approximate calories/serving:
1 slice = 85.

title: barbecued pork steaks
directions: Cut pork steaks in half crosswise, trim off excess fat.
In skillet, brown the steaks on both sides in hot oil; drain steaks on paper toweling.
In 3 1/2 or 4-quart electric slow crockery cooker, arrange onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Sprinkle tapioca over vegetables.
Place pork steaks atop vegetables.
In bowl, combine barbecue sauce, wine and cumin; pour over meat and vegetables in crockery cooker.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 6 to 8 hours or until meat and vegetables are tender.
To serve, transfer meat and vegetables to serving platter.

title: cream pie
directions: Put flour and sugar in bottom of pie shell.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.
Will appear thin, but will thicken as it cools.
Serve warm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine shortening and peanut butter.
Add sugars and blend well.
Add eggs and mix.
Then add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. If peanuts used, add them last.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cheese.
Spray 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking
pan with Pam.
Pour batter into pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Bread will be very moist.

title: gourmet potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes in water until fork tender, not mushy. Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Best served slightly warm. Serves 6.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart cooker.
Cook over low heat until tender.
Add salt to taste.

title: viennese crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, flour, almonds and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape with fingers into crescents and arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 300° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool.
Roll again in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Heat water to boiling stage.
Mix dry ingredients.
Gradually add boiled water to dry ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick.
If it's too thick, add small amounts of water until desired consistency.
Serve with butter and hot biscuits.

title: jambalaya(dirty rice)
directions: Cook rice in 4 cups water.
Set aside.
Peel and cut up eggplant.

Put eggplant, onions, bell pepper and celery in large pot and smother down with 3 tablespoons oil until almost a paste. Cook hamburger, pork chop, ham and chicken breast in pan; add tomatoes and cook for about 20 minutes.
Add rice, meat mixture and seasonings to eggplant mixture.
Let set for about 15 minutes and serve.

title: slow-cooker apple butter
directions: Peel, core and chop apples to measure about 16 cups.
Combine apples and cider in electric slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or until apples are mushy.
Puree in food mill or sieve.
Return pureed mixture to pot.
Add sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Cover and cook on low 1 hour.
Makes 8 cups.

title: ndiwoaza mandanda(egg dish)
directions: Heat oil in deep frying pan.
Add tomatoes and onions.
Mix well.
Add curry powder, salt and cayenne.
Immerse the eggs in mixture.
Add boiling water.
Cover.
Cook slowly for 12 minutes. Serve on rice.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Cook in top of double boiler until tender.

title: bruschetta
directions: Prepare grill or preheat broiler.
Grill bread 1 to 2 minutes, until deep golden.
Rub garlic clove over cut sides of bread. Spoon tomato sauce evenly over top.
Cut into serving pieces. Makes 8 servings.
Preparation time: 15 minutes.
Grilling time: 2 minutes.

title: mexican layered bean dip
directions: Mix beans, chilies and taco seasoning.
Layer bean mixture, taco sauce, sour cream and cheese, and sprinkle with a little taco seasoning.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: nola's bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over All-Bran and set aside.
Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in buttermilk.
Add Bran Buds.
Sift in flour, soda and salt.
Add All-Bran mixture and mix well.

title: meat and potato balls
directions: Mix ground beef, potato and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste. Make into balls and brown in skillet with a little oil.
Brown on all sides, then pour tomato juice over the balls and simmer until done.
Can be served over cooked macaroni or spaghetti.

title: heart burn
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thick rectangle. Sprinkle lightly with garlic and onion powder.
Place slices of ham over all of dough.
Repeat with salami.
Sprinkle each cheese over dough evenly.
Carefully roll dough up lengthwise.
Seal ends and seam to prevent leaking.
Place dough, seam side down, on cookie sheet.
Brush lightly with oil.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into 1-inch slices.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer or by hand. Keep refrigerated. Will last for several weeks. Good with pork roast, turkey and chicken.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Boil the orange
zest
in
a
little salted water until tender; drain.
Combine sugar, water and prepared orange zest. Boil for 10
minutes; cool.
Sift dry ingredients and add egg, milk, nuts and
sugar-zest	syrup.	Place
in
a
greased
5 x 9-inch loaf pan
and
bake	at
300° for 15 minutes.
Increase heat to 350° and bake for 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and oleo.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar. Spread over cooled pretzel mix being sure to seal edges.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries (thawed); mix well.
Allow mixture to jell slightly.
Pour over Cool Whip mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: crab and asparagus bisque
directions: Melt butter or margarine and add onion, peppers, celery and garlic.
Cook gently to soften.
Stir in dry mustard, paprika, cayenne pepper and flour.
Cook about 3 minutes over gentle heat; stir occasionally.
Pour in vegetable stock, gradually stirring until well blended.
Bring to a boil and then reduce heat.
Add asparagus tips.
Simmer about 5 minutes.
Add lump crabmeat and cook about another 5 minutes to ensure asparagus is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste if you wish.
Top with chopped chives before serving and enjoy!

title: 4 layer pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix all ingredients well and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool well before adding second layer.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread coconut and pecans in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Spread batter over coconut and pecans.
Mix the remaining ingredients and spread on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: roasted turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, whisk olive oil with parsley,
thyme,
marjoram, lemon zest, salt and pepper. With fingers, gently separate the skin from the breast meat.

title: harvest relish
directions: In large, nonstick skillet, saute corn in olive oil until slightly brown.
Add zucchini, onion and garlic.
Cook until zucchini is slightly tender (about 1 minute).
Add tomatoes; cover and cook until heated through.
Serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to boil first 3 ingredients.
Mix together next two ingredients and add to the first three.
Cook until clear, remove from heat and add 1 package jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add strawberries, stir and turn into baked pie shell.
Chill a couple hours before serving.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Brown ribs in oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Heat all other ingredients until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over ribs and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: In a 1 pint tightly closed jar, vigorously shake until blended, Ranch dressing mix, oil and dill.
Place oyster crackers in large Tupperware bowl.
Pour dressing mix over crackers and stir until thoroughly coated.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch cake pan or roaster and place in warm oven (250°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir gently 1/2 way through baking.
Allow to cool and store in tightly sealed container.

title: pie crust
directions: Melt oleo in microwave or on stove.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix and press with fingers to line the pie plate.
(Can be mixed in plate you are using for pie).
This crust is also good for a one crust cobbler.
Just place on top of fruit and bake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate the zucchini (do not peel).
Beat oil, eggs and vanilla in blender.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add together the zucchini, egg mixture and dry mixture.
Bake 2 loaves for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken spaghetti(rotel chicken spaghetti)
directions: Boil chicken in onion, bell pepper, celery seed, salt and pepper until cooked.
Remove from water and cool.
Cut into pieces.
In water (chicken broth) boil spaghetti until cooked. Drain.
While spaghetti is boiling, melt butter and cheese in microwave in large bowl.
After melted, add soup and tomatoes. Mix in chicken and spaghetti.
Pour into 9x13 casserole dish. Cover and bake at 350° until bubbles, about 20 minutes.
Can be frozen before baking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar, margarine and milk into a cold electric skillet. Set temperature to 280°.
Boil
5 minutes, stirring constantly. Turn off skillet and add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until melted and blended in.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.

title: cream of beet soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour; cook until mixture bubbles.
Stir in milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Reduce to very low; cook 10 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, beets, salt, pepper and onion juice; heat.
Serve hot.
Top each serving with whipped cream or sour cream.
Garnish with sprig of parsley.
Yields 6 servings or 1/2 cup each.

title: casady's brown sugar bars
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until golden, about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: cinnamon bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: In large bowl, mix 2 cups flour, 6 tablespoons sugar, salt and yeast.
Combine milk, water and 1/3 cup margarine.
Heat 120° to 130° in saucepan.
Add to dry mix; beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat on high 2 minutes.
Stir more flour to make stiff.
Turn on floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and grease top.
Cover and rise until double (35 minutes).
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Punch dough down.
Divide 1/2.
Roll each 1/2 to 14 x 9-inch.
Beat with melted margarine.
Sprinkle 1/2 cinnamon mix. Tightly roll and shape into loaves.
Place in greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover.
Rise until double (35 minutes).
Brush with egg white.
Sprinkle each with 1/2 Crumb Topping.
Loosely top with aluminum tent.
Bake on low rack of oven at 375° for 45 minutes. Remove foil.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Cool on racks.

title: macaroni-beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: party popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugars,
corn syrup, water, vinegar and salt in a 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat and stir. Cook and stir constantly to 260° on a candy thermometer or until syrup forms
a
hard ball in cold water.
Reduce heat and stir in butter.
Pour
syrup in a thin stream over popcorn and stir
until well-coated.
Butter
hands
and
shape
into 3-inch balls.

title: tommie's stuffed cabbage roll
directions: Use 1/2 can soup; mix together with ingredients.
Put mixture into pan boiled cabbage leaves.
Roll up and hold together with a toothpick.
(Will make 6 to 8 rolls.)

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Melt Crisco with all ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° with lid, then 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: monkey bread
directions: Boil 1 cup sugar and all of margarine.
Mix cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Pull apart biscuits into quarters and roll into balls.
Place about 15 at a time into sugar and cinnamon; shake to coat.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix together; spread on thinly sliced boiled ham.
One-half pound of ham makes about 35 Ham Rolls.
Chill and slice.

title: frozen fruit salad #2
directions: In bowl, cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows. Spread in a Pyrex dish.
Freeze overnight.
Will keep indefinitely.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pork satay
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pork).
Cut tenderloin into cubes big enough to grill.
Pour marinade over pork overnight.
Skewer meat with onion and peppers.
Cook on grill or in oven at 375° until brown throughout.

title: chicken macaroni bake
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In medium size kettle, cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Do not brown.
Add soup, milk, pimentos and seasoning.
Stir and cook until smooth.
Combine chicken and macaroni with sauce.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish, then top with cheese.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Mix all ingredients together in brown bag and shake real, real good.
Serve.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix together the cottage cheese and eggs.
Add leftover noodles.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Spread noodle mixture like a crust.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then pour sauce over crust and top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: 15 - 5 and 5 chicken
directions: Into a baking pan or dish place chicken and 5 cans of soup undiluted.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.
Serve with rice. Can use up to 30 pieces of chicken.

title: spaghetti alla carbonara
directions: Unroll pancetta and cut into small cubes.
Put 2 or 3 tablespoons olive oil into a small frying pan.
Add pancetta cubes and fry over medium to low heat (cook slowly) until cooked, but not too hard/crispy.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and roll in a tube shaped roll.
Refrigerate until cold; slice.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter in blazer pan of chafing dish or in pan; blend in flour.
Gradually stir in cream.
Cook slowly on low heat, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add seafood, sherry, lemon juice and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve in pastry shells or over cooked hot rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pork chops mexicana
directions: Brown chops in small amount of oil. Put in 1 x 13-inch pan. Season with seasonings.
Sprinkle rice "around" chops.
Combine season mix, tomato sauce and water.
Pour over chops and rice. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Arrange green pepper and cover.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: cavatini hot dish
directions: Cook the pasta; drain and rinse.
Combine all ingredients, except pepperoni and cheese.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place in 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Arrange pepperoni on the top.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix potatoes with other ingredients. Form into patties. Fry in oil until brown on both sides.

title: salt dough decorations
directions: Mix all ingredients completely with hands.
(If dough is too dry, work in 1 to 1 1/2 teaspoons water.)
Form shapes as desired. Mark all details (facial features, clothing, etc.) on surface of dough with wooden pick or sharp knife.
Dough can be rolled; roll 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Grease four 19 or 16 cans, each about 2 cups.
Beat all ingredients in 3-quart bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds longer.
Pour into cans, filling each about 2/3 full. Cover each tightly with aluminum foil.
Place cans on rack in Dutch oven or steamer; pour boiling water into pan to level of rack. Cover pan.
Keep water boiling over low heat until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 2 1/2 hours (add boiling water during steaming if necessary).
Remove cans from pan; immediately unmold breads.
Serve warm.
Yields 4 loaves.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: In cookie sheet, press out crescent rolls and bake 10 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and mayonnaise well and spread on crust.
Then layer vegetables on top and cheese last.

title: quick slaw
directions: Put slaw mix (precut) in container with lid.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, oil and sugar.
Bring to boil.
Add celery seed. Pour over slaw mix and toss.
Refrigerate and toss occasionally.

title: raccoon
directions: Clean raccoon.
Parboil in clear water and red pepper.
Cook until tender.
Remove from water; season with salt, pepper and garlic (diced).
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mini cinnamon twists
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Spray a baking sheet with Pam. Mix sugar and cinnamon in a small bowl. Separate roll dough into triangles.
Cut each triangle in half lengthwise.
Brush each triangle with melted butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar.
Place a half marshmallow at the wide end of each triangle.
Roll up each triangle starting from the wide end, to enclose the marshmallow. Pinch edges of dough to seal.
Place on baking sheet, seam-side down, about 2-inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Blend confectioners sugar and milk in a small bowl. Drizzle over warm twists.
Remove and place twists on wire rack. Can be frozen in airtight container for up to a month.
May also freeze left over marshmallows for future use.
No need to thaw them up, just use in recipe.
Makes 16 twists.

title: salmon salad loaf
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water.
Stir until softened.
Add boiling water.
Add lemon juice, vinegar, salt, vegetables and then, gently and keeping small chunks intact, mold the salmon. Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on lettuce with a dollop of mayonnaise or yogurt.

title: barbecue for a crowd
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer slowly until thickened.

title: banana chutney
directions: Soak raisins in the vinegar overnight.
Put chopped onions and dates into pan with peeled and sliced bananas.
Add the soaked raisins and vinegar, sugar, salt, turmeric and ginger.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Simmer for approximately 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Bottle and cover in hot sterilized jars.
Makes approximately 5 pounds.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Stir all together.
Let simmer 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is tender.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Grind wafers and nuts fine in food chopper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Roll each ball into size of a cherry and dust with powdered sugar.
Makes 30 to 35 confections that keep indefinitely.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Heat oil for deep frying in wok or fryer.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into bubbling oil.
Turn once. Remove when brown.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare dough for crust; place in pie pan for bottom crust. Mix ingredients together and dot with butter.
Put on top crust and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and then turn down to 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in greased loaf or iron skillet at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with 2 cans of peaches or favorite kind of pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bev's lasagna
directions: Brown beef in oil; add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, until thick (about an hour), stirring occasionally.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Cool to room temperature.
In a bowl, gently stir the butter into mayonnaise, parsley, curry powder, garlic, marjoram, salt and pepper. In a large bowl combine chicken, grapes and almonds.
Arrange this mixture on lettuce leaves.
Spoon dressing on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 4.

title: heidi's meat loaf
directions: In a blender or food processor, pulverize the onion in the milk. Add spices and egg. Mix into the ground meat. Add bread crumbs. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and baking powder.
Stir in cream and eggs.
Drop from a large spoon onto a well-greased hot pan.
Brown on both sides in bacon drippings.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown beef and drain off excess fat.
Precook potatoes and carrots about 5 to 10 minutes.
Put beef in a large, heavy pot; add water and drained vegetables, green pepper and onion. Sprinkle in seasonings and stir to blend.
Simmer over low heat 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serves 12.

title: fried pumpkin
directions: Cut and seed pumpkin.
Cut into cubes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Coat well with flour and meal mixture.
Deep fry.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix soup with 1 can water.
Combine rice, hamburger, onion, seasonings and 4 tablespoons soup; mix well.
Form into balls. Place in casserole dish.
Cover with remaining soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover last 15 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: spinach and artichoke stuffed shells
directions: Cook spinach and artichoke hearts as directed on packages. Drain well.
Chop artichoke hearts.
Set aside.
Cook pasta shells as directed.
Drain and set aside.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand 1 hour to blend flavors. Serve over cubed bananas.

title: fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
After it reaches boiling point, reduce heat and do not stir.
Test by dropping a small drop in a cup of cold water.
When it reaches a hard ball stage, it will be done.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until cool. Pour in buttered dish.
Cut into small squares.

title: golden crumb broccoli
directions: Cut and cook broccoli in salted water for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain well. Put into casserole dish. Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, pimento and lemon juice. Pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese cracker crumbs. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled and melted margarine and vanilla or anise.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to egg mixture.
Dough will be sticky enough to be dropped by spoon on griddle.
Makes 60 pizzelles.
Can add walnuts or pecans if desired.

title: spinach and rice
directions: Saute spinach and onion in margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients (except bread crumbs).
Place in buttered casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix walnuts, dates, baking soda and salt together with a fork. Add shortening and water; let stand 20 minutes.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add vanilla, then sugar and flour; beat with fork.
Add date mixture, just enough to blend.

title: meatballs
directions: In saucepan mix to taste, ketchup, brown sugar, just a little Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper and let simmer.
Take the hamburger, minced onion, salt and pepper and mix together and roll into meatballs.
Broil and drain off grease.
Put meatballs in sauce and simmer until ready to serve.
(Sauce can be made in crock-pot.)

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: honey and flaxseed bread(for the bread machine)
directions: Put all ingredients in the pan in the order listed, or in the reverse order if the manual for your machine specifies dry ingredients first and liquids last.
Select Basic Wheat cycle, Light setting (or the equivalent setting for your machine).
Press Start and in about 3 1/2 to 4 hours you'll have a delicious loaf of whole grain bread.
Makes one 1 1/2 pound loaf.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for an hour or so.

title: malibu layered salad
directions: Add ingredients in layers; put lettuce, onions, peas and mayonnaise (with sugar mixed in) into 13 x 9-inch glass cake dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: sauce piquante
directions: Cut up sausage.
Brown on both sides.
Take out sausage and drain on paper towels.
Brown chicken on both sides in sausage grease.
Take chicken out of skillet.
Cut up onions and simmer in skillet.
Put meat back in skillet and add all other ingredients. Season to taste.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese candy mints
directions: Mash cream cheese.
Add powdered sugar gradually until the candy mixture becomes like stiff pie dough, approximately 3 1/4 cups.
Add desired flavorings like mint or peppermint and any colors.
Roll in granulated sugar, put on wax paper and flatten with a fork.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: mississippi mud
directions: *It is richer with 2 jars of Marshmallow Creme.

title: southern no knead rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the warm water.
Add the eggs (well beaten) and the sugar.
Stir in the melted margarine (1 stick), salt and flour.
Let rise until double, about 3 hours.
Punch down.
Make out and let stand for about 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
They brown well if brushed with butter.

title: cream of wheat bread(diabetic)
directions: Mix and cook as cornbread.
Cook in a hot, prepared skillet.

title: cheese-mushroom strata
directions: In large bowl, beat together eggs, broth, sour cream and mustard.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and mushrooms.
Pour into greased 2-quart oval or 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meat and marinate at least 2 hours in refrigerator.
(Use for meats or chicken.)

title: potatoes celeste
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; top with crumbs and butter.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Then mix in dry ingredients, mashed bananas and chopped nuts.
Mix only until blended.
Pour into one regular-size greased loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on size of pan.
Use toothpick, inserted into center of loaf, to test for doneness.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool.
Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add to first mixture.
Add beaten eggs.
Stir in 4 cups flour.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining 4 cups flour.
Knead slightly.
Grease top and cover bowl.
Store in icebox.
As needed, make small balls and let rise on an ungreased cookie sheet 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stays fresh in icebox for 1 week.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: kathy's instant cocoa
directions: This make a lot!!!

title: lamb chops with vegetables(low calorie)
directions: Trim excess fat from meat.
Lightly grease large skillet, brown meat.
Drain off fat.
Measure reserved vegetable liquid; if necessary, add water to measure 3/4 cup liquid.
Stir liquid, soy sauce, bouillon cubes and garlic into skillet; heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Add onion; cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Remove meat.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Stir gradually into skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in green pepper, Chinese vegetables and water chestnuts.
Add meat and tomatoes.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings at 240 calories each.

title: roast with wine
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over a 3 to 5 pound beef roast. Cook in 350° oven for 4 hours.

title: cheese and mostaccioli
directions: Cook and butter noodles.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Layer noodles, Mozzarella cheese and American cheese, continuing and ending with noodles on top.
Pour 1 can chopped stewed tomatoes over all.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: buckeyes
directions: *May substitute 2 pounds semi-sweet melting caps (doesn't need paraffin).

title: homestyle chicken and biscuit dumplings
directions: Will need 1 Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased loaf pans, filling pans only 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie(southern)
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, salt, butter and vanilla together.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Sprinkle pecans over filling and bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and pepper in butter or margarine.
Add meat and brown.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook noodles and drain.
In another bowl, combine cheeses and sour cream.
Put half of noodles in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread cheese mixture over this, top with remaining noodles and cover this with meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can cook this ahead and then warm up before serving.
Can also be frozen.

title: crispy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Stir together the cooked rice and next 10 ingredients in a bowl. Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with cereal. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden and bubbly. Garnish if desired.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Make into a ball.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Before serving, cover with nuts.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook until soft ball.
Add oleo and vanilla after cooked.

title: salsa
directions: Blend all above ingredients together.
Let sit in refrigerator for three days for best flavor.

title: blueberry chess pie
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and salt until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, cornstarch, vinegar and vanilla, beating until smooth. Stir in blueberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 300° and bake an additional 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together except cake mix, butter and pecans.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan and pour mixture into it. Sprinkle nuts and cake mix on top of mixture.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or plain frosting.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Grate sweet potatoes very fine; add sugar and eggs, one at a time, beating well; then milk.
Add coconut and raisins.
Bake in large greased casserole or pudding pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Serves 10 or 12 people.

title: chocolate banana shake
directions: Place banana, corn syrup, cocoa and water in blender container; cover.
Blend on high speed 1 minute or until smooth. Add milk, ice cream and vanilla; cover.
Blend 1 minute longer or until smooth.
Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: fried pie pastry
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll in small balls, then roll flat and put fruit in center; fold over and seal. Fry in deep grease.

title: jewel's chocolate icing
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Take from heat. Add vanilla.
Cool, then beat to spreading consistency.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine oil, sugar, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add milk, egg, oat bran, oatmeal and wheat germ.
Mix lightly with wooden spoon to moisten.
Stir in blueberries.
Fill paper lined muffin tin 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown.

title: low calorie grilled chicken
directions: Clean chicken breasts.
Place in large bowl and pour dressing over the top; let it soak for several hours.
The longer, the better.
Place chicken on grill and cook on medium to low heat so chicken will not burn.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread evenly in square pan the apples. Sprinkle them with water, cinnamon and salt.
With pastry blender, mix the sugar, flour and soft butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: lone star refritos
directions: Heat a cast-iron frying pan on medium-high and add margarine. Saute onion and jalapenos for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add garlic and saute for 1 minute.
Add the beans and herbs.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mash bean mixture in pan until pastry.
Stir in cheese and continue heating for 1 minute.
Serve hot with warm tortillas and salsa.

title: colonel sanders' "butter thin" pancakes
directions: Mix coffee cream and eggs.
In separate bowl, mix baking powder, salt and flour.
Mix both mixtures together. Then add hot butter.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine the eggs, Pecorino Romano cheese, parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
In a medium skillet, heat the oil over medium-high heat.
Dredge both sides of each chicken breast into the flour, making sure to remove any extra flour, then into the egg mixture and then into the breadcrumbs.
Saute the chicken in the hot oil for approximately 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown and fully cooked.
Place the tomato sauce in a shallow baking dish and arrange the chicken on the sauce.
Spoon the remaining sauce over the chicken.
Sprinkle one tablespoon of Parmesan cheese over each piece of chicken.
Top each one with a slice of Mozzarella cheese.

title: dill pickle pinwheels(appetizers)
directions: Soften cream cheese. Drain pickles and cut each into pieces approximately 1/2-inch. Spread a thin layer of cream cheese over each Buddig thin sliced meat slices. Cut meat into strips approximately 1/2-inch wide.
Roll up each pickle piece in strip of cheese spread and meat. Secure with toothpick.
Serve chilled.

title: dessert crust (alternative to graham cracker)
directions: Stir all ingredients well and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 pie tins.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: corned beef soup
directions: Cut all ingredients into bite-size pieces.
Put in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Cook until tender, about 30 minutes.

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with basil and pepper.
Mix together soy sauce, ketchup, honey, corn oil and garlic.
Place chicken, skin side up, in shallow baking pan.
Baste with sauce.
Bake in 350° oven or cook on barbecue grill, basting often.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine undiluted orange juice and milk with mixer, then add pudding.
Beat on low speed 2 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and chill 2 or 3 hours.
Drain the fruit well before dipping.

title: curried rice and artichoke salad
directions: Mix together last 3 ingredients. Cook Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box. Let rice cool, then add chopped vegetables. Stir in mayonnaise/marinade mix and refrigerate.

title: red party punch
directions: Mix. Add a bag of ice. Enjoy.

title: raisin-brandy sauce
directions: After frying slices of country ham, drain off the excess grease and add a little water to the drippings.
Scrape the water and drippings together with a metal spatula and then add a tablespoon of strong coffee.
Boil this liquid mixture and serve along with the sliced ham.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Partially freeze steak and slice across the grain into 2 x 1/4-inch strips.

title: diabetic raisin applesauce cake
directions: Cook raisins in 2 cups water for 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix eggs, oil and applesauce.
Add the dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add the raisins.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans in oven at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or in Bundt pan.

title: french-style bavarian mint coffee mix
directions: Blend ingredients in blender.
Use 1 tablespoon to 3/4 cup boiling water for 1 serving.
Serve with a peppermint stick and a dollop of whipped cream.

title: ma's potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables until tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain excess water.
Add seasonings.
You may want to mash vegetables slightly. Add milk.
Heat thoroughly but don't boil.
Garnish when ladled into bowls with sour cream, bacon bits, diced fresh onion, croutons, grated cheese or parsley.

title: 30 day friendship cake
directions: Stir together in a gallon jar and cover loosely.
Stir everyday until the 10th day.

title: quick black forest fondue
directions: Drain cherries and set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and evaporated milk.
Stir lightly.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat. Add almond extract. Pour into fondue pot or chafing dish.
Dip cherries into warm fondue.
Um Um! Makes 1 1/2 cups fondue.

title: chicken poppy seed casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and shred into the bottom of a casserole dish.
Mix together sour cream and soup.
Pour over the top of the chicken.
Sprinkle crackers on the top and pour melted butter over crackers.
(Sprinkle with poppy seeds.)
Bake at 325 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add
apple.
Add	eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Add raisins last.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: super spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach completely and squeeze to remove all of the water.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill at least 6 hours before serving.

title: chicken and rice in a dish
directions: Combine soup, sour cream, milk and basil.
Measure 1/2 cup of soup mixture; set to side.
Combine remaining soup mixture and rice.
Spread in bottom of a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Rinse broccoli spears with water to separate.
Arrange broccoli spears and chicken over rice mixture.
Spoon reserved sauce over all.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until chicken and rice are tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: broccoli and shrimp casserole
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery.
Saute in butter until tender.
Add mushroom soup, cheese, broccoli, cooked rice, milk and shrimp.
Pour in 3-quart casserole dish.
Cover; cook in microwave for 25 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: grandma's raw cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in 2 cups hot water.
Stir in 2 cups raw cranberries, which have been washed and ground.
Let partly cool and add chopped celery and black walnuts.

title: birmingham bash
directions: Boil water and sugar for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix sugar, water, orange juice, lemonade and alcohol.
Freeze until slushy.
Mix 1/4 to 1/2 cup slush with 3/4 to 1/2 cup soda or 7-Up.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Stir together flour, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, oil and vanilla; stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts, if wanted.
Pour into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square or 8-inch round pan.
Combine 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour over batter in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Serve warm or chill.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add juice and rind of lemon, egg yolks, flour and milk.
Stir well.
Fold in beaten whites.
Bake in pan of hot water in oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: creamy pineapple squares
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in
boiling water.
Chill until thick but not
set.
Drain
pineapple reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Fold pineapple
and
pecans into gelatin mixture.
Pour into lightly oiled 9-inch square pan.
Chill until almost set, then dissolve gelatin
in
water.
Add
reserved pineapple liquid.
Gradually add to cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Pour over lime gelatin layer.
Chill until firm.

title: frog eye salad(makes 25 servings)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Cool mixture.
Bring water to a boil. Add the other teaspoon salt and oil.
Add acini de pepe.
Cook at rolling boil until they are done.
They should look clear.
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.
Cool very well.
Add egg mixture into acini de pepe.
Mix lightly, but thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Add fruit and Cool Whip.
Can be refrigerated for as long as a week.
Keep in airtight container.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add remaining ingredients and work into a stiff dough. Pinch off a small amount and roll thin between the palms. Curve like a horseshoe; place on cookie sheet fairly close together. Bake at 350° until light golden brown. Roll in powdered sugar while hot. Cool and store in a cool place.

title: dill pickle brine
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour over clean cucumbers, garlic clove and dill in clean jars. Seal jars.
Set in dark cupboard for 2 months.

title: orange chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place breast into a roasting pan. Place the orange into the middle of the roasting pan among the breasts.
Mix together the orange juice, salt, pepper and ginger. Pour over the chicken.
Roast for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn over.
Smear chicken breasts with honey.
Baste with pan juices.
Cook for 20 minutes more or until done.

title: oven french fries
directions: Cut potatoes into julienne strips.
Place in bowl and toss with oil and seasonings.
Spread on nonstick baking sheet and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serves 4.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated
milk and butter in 3-quart casserole.
Cook on Full power for 10 to 13 minutes or until soft ball stage is reached*.
Stir mixture 3 times during cooking time. Beat in marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla with wire whip until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.

title: overnight salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed. Cover pea layer with mayonnaise. Spread to cover. Sprinkle mayonnaise with sugar. Top with layer of cheese, then with bacon bits. Sprinkle Salad Supreme generously. Refrigerate overnight. Do not stir. Spoon out servings of all layers.

title: sunrise cake
directions: Beat eggs until very fluffy. Add sugar slowly and then add oil. Add flour gradually. Beat 6 or 7 minutes. Add orange, lemon and peppermint flavorings and mix well. Grease and flour tube pan. Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Add water to frozen concentrates as directed on can and mix all together.
Serve in punch bowl over ice cubes/ring (if desired).
Serves 50.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Drain thawed broccoli on paper towels.
Stir soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise until blended.
Stir in drained broccoli and chopped water chestnuts.
Cover; chill for 2 hours.
Stir before serving with chunks of breads as an appetizer.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Brown meat, onions and green pepper.
Add tomatoes, paste, sugar and seasoning.
Mix cooked spaghetti, margarine, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Top with meat mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle grated Mozzarella on top and bake 5 minutes more.

title: banana loaf
directions: Let oleo stand (room temperature).
Cream oleo and sugar, then bananas.
Beat 1 minute.
Add eggs and flour and beat 1 or 2 minutes.
Then add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Beat.
Bake in greased, slightly floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: (Leftover ham or cooked seafood can be added for an even heartier meal.)

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Roll into balls.
Then roll into mixture of 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
